svcTlsBgpADAdminStatus.name: svcTlsBgpADAdminStatus
svcTlsBgpADAdminStatus.description: The value of svcTlsBgpADAdminStatus specifies the desired administrative state for BGP Auto-Discovery in this VPLS service.

svcEpipePbbTableLastChanged.name: svcEpipePbbTableLastChanged
svcEpipePbbTableLastChanged.description: The value of svcEpipePbbTableLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of svcEpipePbbTable. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcEpipePbbTable.name: svcEpipePbbTable
svcEpipePbbTable.description: The svcEpipePbbTable contains objects related to Provider Backbone Bridging (PBB) feature as relates to 'epipe' services. Entries are created and destroyed using svcEpipePbbRowStatus object.

svcEpipePbbEntry.name: svcEpipePbbEntry
svcEpipePbbEntry.description: Each row entry contains objects that allows the modification of the PBB objects for an 'epipe' service.

svcEpipePbbRowStatus.name: svcEpipePbbRowStatus
svcEpipePbbRowStatus.description: The value of svcEpipePbbRowStatus is used for the creation and deletion of Provider Backbone Bridging information in a EPIPE service. To create an entry in the table, svcEpipePbbBvplsSvcId, svcEpipePbbSvcISID objects must be set along with svcEpipePbbBvplsDstMac or svcEpipePbbBvplsDstMacName object set to non-default value.

svcEpipePbbLastChngd.name: svcEpipePbbLastChngd
svcEpipePbbLastChngd.description: The value of svcEpipePbbLastChngd indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of this entry. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcEpipePbbBvplsSvcId.name: svcEpipePbbBvplsSvcId
svcEpipePbbBvplsSvcId.description: The value of svcEpipePbbBvplsSvcId specifies the Backbone-VPLS service for the PBB tunnel associated with this service. This object must be set at the creation time and can not be modified later.

svcEpipePbbBvplsDstMac.name: svcEpipePbbBvplsDstMac
svcEpipePbbBvplsDstMac.description: The value of svcEpipePbbBvplsDstMac specifies the Backbone Destination MAC-Address for Provider Backbone Bridging packets. An 'inconsistentValue' error is returned if svcEpipePbbBvplsDstMac or svcEpipePbbBvplsDstMacName object is not set to non-default value.

svcEpipePbbSvcISID.name: svcEpipePbbSvcISID
svcEpipePbbSvcISID.description: The value of the object svcEpipePbbSvcISID specifies a 24 bit (0..16777215) service instance identifier for the PBB tunnel associated with this service. As part of the Provider Backbone Bridging frames, it is used at the destination PE as a demultiplexor field. This object must be set along with svcEpipePbbBvplsSvcId.

svcEpipePbbOperState.name: svcEpipePbbOperState
svcEpipePbbOperState.description: The value of the object svcEpipePbbOperState indicates the operating state of PBB tunnel associated with this service.

svcEpipePbbFlooding.name: svcEpipePbbFlooding
svcEpipePbbFlooding.description: The value of the object svcEpipePbbFlooding indicates the state for traffic flowing into the Backbone-VPLS through PBB tunnel. If the backbone-destination MAC is found in the FDB of Backbone-VPLS then traffic will be sent to specific SAP/SDP and this object will be set to 'false'. In case of SPB Managed Backbone-VPLS, if backbone-destination MAC is not found in the FDB of Backbone-VPLS then traffic will not be sent out of any SAP/SDP and this object will be set to 'false'. Otherwise, traffic will be flooded to all SAP/SDP bindings in the Backbone-VPLS and the object will be set to 'true'.

svcEpipePbbLastStatusChange.name: svcEpipePbbLastStatusChange
svcEpipePbbLastStatusChange.description: The value of the object svcEpipePbbLastStatusChange indicates the value of sysUpTime at the time of the most recent operating status change to this tunnel.

svcEpipePbbBvplsOperDstMac.name: svcEpipePbbBvplsOperDstMac
svcEpipePbbBvplsOperDstMac.description: The value of svcEpipePbbBvplsOperDstMac indicates the operational Backbone Destination MAC-Address for Provider Backbone Bridging packets.

svcEpipePbbBvplsDstMacName.name: svcEpipePbbBvplsDstMacName
svcEpipePbbBvplsDstMacName.description: The value of svcEpipePbbBvplsDstMacName specifies the Backbone Destination MAC-Address-Name for Provider Backbone Bridging packets. An 'inconsistentValue' error is returned if svcEpipePbbBvplsDstMac or svcEpipePbbBvplsDstMacName object is not set to non-default value.

tlsPipInfoTable.name: tlsPipInfoTable
tlsPipInfoTable.description: A table that contains TLS PIP (Provider Internal Port) uplink information. PIP is the virtual link between I and B components of PBB (Provider Backbone Bridging) model. I component refers to a service with svcVplsType set to 'iVpls (3)' and B component refers to a service with svcVplsType set to 'bVpls (2)'. When any form of STP is enabled in the iVpls domain, the PIP uplink is modeled as a regular STP port.

tlsPipInfoEntry.name: tlsPipInfoEntry
tlsPipInfoEntry.description: TLS specific information about PIP uplink.

tlsPipStpPortState.name: tlsPipStpPortState
tlsPipStpPortState.description: The value of tlsPipStpPortState indicates the PIP uplink's current state as defined by application of the Spanning Tree Protocol. This state controls what action PIP uplink takes on reception of a frame. If the bridge has detected a port that is malfunctioning it will place that port into the 'broken (6)' state.

tlsPipStpPortRole.name: tlsPipStpPortRole
tlsPipStpPortRole.description: The value of tlsPipStpPortRole indicates the current role of the PIP uplink as defined by the Rapid Spanning Tree Protocol.

tlsPipStpDesignatedBridge.name: tlsPipStpDesignatedBridge
tlsPipStpDesignatedBridge.description: The value of tlsPipStpDesignatedBridge indicates the Bridge Identifier of the bridge which this PIP uplink considers to be the Designated Bridge for this port's segment.

tlsPipStpDesignatedPort.name: tlsPipStpDesignatedPort
tlsPipStpDesignatedPort.description: The value of tlsPipStpDesignatedPort indicates the Port Identifier of the port on the Designated Bridge for this port's segment.

tlsPipStpException.name: tlsPipStpException
tlsPipStpException.description: The value of the object tlsPipStpException indicates whether an STP exception condition is present on this Pip. - none : no exception condition found. - oneWayCommuniation : The neighbor RSTP peer on this link is not able to detect our presence. - downstreamLoopDetected :A loop is detected on this link.

tlsPipStpForwardTransitions.name: tlsPipStpForwardTransitions
tlsPipStpForwardTransitions.description: The value of the object tlsPipStpForwardTransitions indicates the number of times this port has transitioned from the Learning state to the Forwarding state.

tlsPipStpInConfigBpdus.name: tlsPipStpInConfigBpdus
tlsPipStpInConfigBpdus.description: The value of the object tlsPipStpInConfigBpdus indicates the number of Configuration BPDUs received on this PIP uplink.

tlsPipStpInTcnBpdus.name: tlsPipStpInTcnBpdus
tlsPipStpInTcnBpdus.description: The value of the object tlsPipStpInTcnBpdus indicates the number of Topology Change Notification BPDUs received on this PIP uplink.

tlsPipStpInRstBpdus.name: tlsPipStpInRstBpdus
tlsPipStpInRstBpdus.description: The value of the object tlsPipStpInRstBpdus indicates the number of Rapid Spanning Tree (RST) BPDUs received on this PIP uplink.

tlsPipStpInMstBpdus.name: tlsPipStpInMstBpdus
tlsPipStpInMstBpdus.description: The value of the object tlsPipStpInMstBpdus indicates the number of Multiple Spanning Tree (MST) BPDUs received on this PIP uplink.

tlsPipStpInBadBpdus.name: tlsPipStpInBadBpdus
tlsPipStpInBadBpdus.description: This object specifies the number of bad BPDUs received on this PIP uplink.

tlsPipStpOutConfigBpdus.name: tlsPipStpOutConfigBpdus
tlsPipStpOutConfigBpdus.description: The value of the object tlsPipStpOutConfigBpdus indicates the number of Configuration BPDUs sent out this PIP uplink.

tlsPipStpOutTcnBpdus.name: tlsPipStpOutTcnBpdus
tlsPipStpOutTcnBpdus.description: This object specifies the number of Topology Change Notification BPDUs sent out this PIP uplink.

tlsPipStpOutRstBpdus.name: tlsPipStpOutRstBpdus
tlsPipStpOutRstBpdus.description: The value of the object tlsPipStpOutRstBpdus indicates the number of Rapid Spanning Tree (RST) BPDUs sent out on this PIP uplink.

tlsPipStpOutMstBpdus.name: tlsPipStpOutMstBpdus
tlsPipStpOutMstBpdus.description: The value of the object tlsPipStpOutMstBpdus indicates the number of Multiple Spanning Tree (MST) BPDUs sent out on this PIP uplink.

tlsPipStpOperStatus.name: tlsPipStpOperStatus
tlsPipStpOperStatus.description: The value of the object tlsPipStpOperStatus indicates the operational status of this PIP uplink.

tlsPipStpMvplsPruneState.name: tlsPipStpMvplsPruneState
tlsPipStpMvplsPruneState.description: The value of tlsPipStpMvplsPruneState indicates the mVPLS prune state of this PIP uplink. The state reflects whether or not this uplink is pruned by the STP instance running in the mVPLS instance.

tlsPipStpOperProtocol.name: tlsPipStpOperProtocol
tlsPipStpOperProtocol.description: The value of tlsPipStpOperProtocol indicates whether 'stp', 'rstp' or 'mstp' is running on this PIP uplink. If the protocol is not enabled on this PIP uplink, the value 'notApplicable' is returned.

tlsPipStpPortNum.name: tlsPipStpPortNum
tlsPipStpPortNum.description: The value of the object tlsPipStpPortNum specifies the value of the port number field which is contained in the least significant 12 bits of the 16-bit Port ID associated with this PIP uplink.

tlsPipStpInsideRegion.name: tlsPipStpInsideRegion
tlsPipStpInsideRegion.description: The value of the object tlsPipStpInsideRegion indicates whether the network connected to the PIP is in the same MST region. It corresponds to the parameter 'infoInternal' in 802.1Q.

tlsPipInTcBitBpdus.name: tlsPipInTcBitBpdus
tlsPipInTcBitBpdus.description: The value of the object tlsPipInTcBitBpdus indicates the number of BPDUs received on this PIP uplink with the Topology Change bit set.

tlsPipOutTcBitBpdus.name: tlsPipOutTcBitBpdus
tlsPipOutTcBitBpdus.description: This object specifies the number of BPDUs sent out this PIP uplink with the Topology Change bit set.

tlsPipMstiTable.name: tlsPipMstiTable
tlsPipMstiTable.description: This table contains Multiple Spanning Tree Instance information for the PIP uplink. Each management VPLS running MSTP can have upto 15 MSTI. An entry in this table is automatically created when a tlsMstiEntry is created.

tlsPipMstiEntry.name: tlsPipMstiEntry
tlsPipMstiEntry.description: Information about a specific MSTI for a PIP uplink.

tlsPipMstiPortRole.name: tlsPipMstiPortRole
tlsPipMstiPortRole.description: tlsPipMstiPortRole indicates the current role of the PIP uplink in the MSTI as defined by the Spanning Tree Protocol.

tlsPipMstiPortState.name: tlsPipMstiPortState
tlsPipMstiPortState.description: The value of the object tlsPipMstiPortState indicates the port's current state as defined by application of the Spanning Tree Protocol. This state controls what action a port takes on reception of a frame. If the bridge has detected a port that is malfunctioning it will place that port into the broken(6) state.

tlsPipMstiDesignatedBridge.name: tlsPipMstiDesignatedBridge
tlsPipMstiDesignatedBridge.description: The value of the object tlsPipMstiDesignatedBridge indicates the Bridge Identifier of the bridge which this port considers to be the Designated Bridge for this port's segment for this MSTI.

tlsPipMstiDesignatedPort.name: tlsPipMstiDesignatedPort
tlsPipMstiDesignatedPort.description: The value of the object tlsPipMstiDesignatedPort indicates the Port Identifier of the port on the Designated Bridge for this port's segment for this MSTI.

svcTotalFdbMimDestIdxEntries.name: svcTotalFdbMimDestIdxEntries
svcTotalFdbMimDestIdxEntries.description: The value of the object svcTotalFdbMimDestIdxEntries indicates the number of system wide Backbone MAC address indices in use.

svcDhcpManagedRouteTable.name: svcDhcpManagedRouteTable
svcDhcpManagedRouteTable.description: A table that contains DHCP managed routes.

svcDhcpManagedRouteInetAddrType.name: svcDhcpManagedRouteInetAddrType
svcDhcpManagedRouteInetAddrType.description: The value of svcDhcpManagedRouteInetAddrType indicates the address type of svcDhcpManagedRouteInetAddr.

svcDhcpManagedRouteInetAddr.name: svcDhcpManagedRouteInetAddr
svcDhcpManagedRouteInetAddr.description: The value of svcDhcpManagedRouteInetAddr indicates the IP address of the managed route.

svcDhcpManagedRoutePrefixLen.name: svcDhcpManagedRoutePrefixLen
svcDhcpManagedRoutePrefixLen.description: The value of svcDhcpManagedRoutePrefixLen indicates the prefix length of the subnet associated with svcDhcpManagedRouteInetAddr.

svcDhcpManagedRouteStatus.name: svcDhcpManagedRouteStatus
svcDhcpManagedRouteStatus.description: The value of svcDhcpManagedRouteStatus indicates the state of this managed route.

svcArpHostTableLastChanged.name: svcArpHostTableLastChanged
svcArpHostTableLastChanged.description: The value of svcArpHostTableLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of an entry in the svcArpHostTable. If there were no changes in the table since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcArpHostTable.name: svcArpHostTable
svcArpHostTable.description: A table that contains ARP hosts.

svcArpHostEntry.name: svcArpHostEntry
svcArpHostEntry.description: Information about a specific ARP host.

svcArpHostIpAddrType.name: svcArpHostIpAddrType
svcArpHostIpAddrType.description: The value of svcArpHostIpAddrType indicates the address type of svcArpHostIpAddr.

svcArpHostIpAddr.name: svcArpHostIpAddr
svcArpHostIpAddr.description: The value of svcArpHostIpAddr indicates the IP address of the ARP host.

svcArpHostLocale.name: svcArpHostLocale
svcArpHostLocale.description: The value of svcArpHostLocale indicates if the ARP Host is learned via a SAP or spoke SDP.

svcArpHostSapPortId.name: svcArpHostSapPortId
svcArpHostSapPortId.description: When the value of svcArpHostLocale is 'sap', the object svcArpHostSapPortId along with the object svcArpHostSapEncapValue, indicates the SAP where this ARP host is learned. This object is otherwise insignificant and contains the value 0.

svcArpHostSapEncapValue.name: svcArpHostSapEncapValue
svcArpHostSapEncapValue.description: When the value of svcArpHostLocale is 'sap', the object svcArpHostSapPortId along with the object svcArpHostSapEncapValue, indicates the SAP where this ARP host is learned. This object is otherwise insignificant and contains the value 0.

svcArpHostSdpId.name: svcArpHostSdpId
svcArpHostSdpId.description: When the value of svcArpHostLocale is 'sdp', the object svcArpHostSdpId, along with the object svcArpHostVcId, indicates the SDP Binding where this ARP host is learned. This object is otherwise insignificant and contains the value 0.

svcArpHostVcId.name: svcArpHostVcId
svcArpHostVcId.description: When the value of svcArpHostLocale is 'sdp', the object svcArpHostVcId, along with the object svcArpHostSdpId, indicates the SDP Binding where this ARP host is learned. This object is otherwise insignificant and contains the value 0.

svcArpHostSessionTimeout.name: svcArpHostSessionTimeout
svcArpHostSessionTimeout.description: The value of svcArpHostSessionTimeout indicates the session timeout of this ARP host. The session timeout can be configured in the Radius server. If no session timeout is specified, its value is equal to the value of the object svcArpHostDefaultSessionTimeout.

svcArpHostStart.name: svcArpHostStart
svcArpHostStart.description: The value of svcArpHostStart indicates the time of the creation of this entry.

svcArpHostLastAuth.name: svcArpHostLastAuth
svcArpHostLastAuth.description: The value of svcArpHostLastAuth indicates the time of the last authentication.

svcArpHostRefresh.name: svcArpHostRefresh
svcArpHostRefresh.description: The value of svcArpHostRefresh indicates the time of the last refresh of this ARP host. Note that not every refresh requires authentication.

svcArpHostRemainingTime.name: svcArpHostRemainingTime
svcArpHostRemainingTime.description: The value of svcArpHostRemainingTime indicates the remaining time of this ARP host.

svcArpHostShcvOperState.name: svcArpHostShcvOperState
svcArpHostShcvOperState.description: The value of svcArpHostShcvOperState indicates the state of the subscriber host connectivity check for this ARP host.

svcArpHostShcvChecks.name: svcArpHostShcvChecks
svcArpHostShcvChecks.description: The value of svcArpHostShcvChecks indicates the number of host connectivity check requests for this ARP host.

svcArpHostShcvReplies.name: svcArpHostShcvReplies
svcArpHostShcvReplies.description: The value of svcArpHostShcvReplies indicates the number of host connectivity replies for this ARP host.

svcArpHostShcvReplyTime.name: svcArpHostShcvReplyTime
svcArpHostShcvReplyTime.description: The value of svcArpHostShcvReplyTime indicates the time of the last successful host connectivity check for this ARP host.

svcArpHostSubscrIdent.name: svcArpHostSubscrIdent
svcArpHostSubscrIdent.description: The value of svcArpHostSubscrIdent indicates the id of the parent subscriber of this ARP host.

svcArpHostSubProfString.name: svcArpHostSubProfString
svcArpHostSubProfString.description: The value of svcArpHostSubProfString indicates the subscriber profile string applicable for this ARP host.

svcArpHostSlaProfString.name: svcArpHostSlaProfString
svcArpHostSlaProfString.description: The value of svcArpHostSlaProfString indicates the SLA profile string applicable for this ARP host.

svcArpHostAppProfString.name: svcArpHostAppProfString
svcArpHostAppProfString.description: The value of svcArpHostAppProfString indicates the application profile string applicable for this ARP host.

svcArpHostAncpString.name: svcArpHostAncpString
svcArpHostAncpString.description: The object svcArpHostAncpString indicates the value of the ANCP-string received from the RADIUS server.

svcArpHostInterDestId.name: svcArpHostInterDestId
svcArpHostInterDestId.description: The object svcArpHostInterDestId indicates the intermediate destination identifier received from the RADIUS server.

svcArpHostRetailerSvcId.name: svcArpHostRetailerSvcId
svcArpHostRetailerSvcId.description: The value of svcArpHostRetailerSvcId indicates the service ID of the retailer VPRN service to which this ARP host belongs. When this object is non zero, the ARP host belongs to a retailer VPRN.

svcArpHostRetailerIf.name: svcArpHostRetailerIf
svcArpHostRetailerIf.description: The value of svcArpHostRetailerIf indicates the interface index of the retailer VPRN interface to which this ARP host belongs. When this object is non zero, the ARP host belongs to a retailer VPRN.

svcArpHostMacAddr.name: svcArpHostMacAddr
svcArpHostMacAddr.description: The value of svcArpHostMacAddr indicates the MAC address of this ARP host.

svcArpHostPersistKey.name: svcArpHostPersistKey
svcArpHostPersistKey.description: The value of svcArpHostPersistKey indicates a key value that can be used to track this ARP host in the persistence file.

svcArpHostCategoryMapName.name: svcArpHostCategoryMapName
svcArpHostCategoryMapName.description: The object svcArpHostCategoryMapName indicates the value of the category map name received from the RADIUS server.

svcArpHostRadiusClassAttr.name: svcArpHostRadiusClassAttr
svcArpHostRadiusClassAttr.description: The value of svcArpHostRadiusClassAttr indicates the Class attribute returned by the RADIUS server in an Access-Accept message. If no RADIUS authentication is performed for this ARP host, or RADIUS did not return this attribute, the value of this object is empty.

svcArpHostRadiusUserName.name: svcArpHostRadiusUserName
svcArpHostRadiusUserName.description: The value of svcArpHostRadiusUserName indicates the User-Name attribute returned by the RADIUS server in an Access-Accept message. If RADIUS did not return this attribute, the value of this object is equal to the User-Name attribute sent in the original Access-Request message. If no RADIUS authentication is performed for this ARP host, the value of this object is empty.

svcArpHostOriginSubscrId.name: svcArpHostOriginSubscrId
svcArpHostOriginSubscrId.description: The value of svcArpHostOriginSubscrId indicates which source provided the subscriber-id.

svcArpHostOriginStrings.name: svcArpHostOriginStrings
svcArpHostOriginStrings.description: The value of svcArpHostOriginStrings indicates which server provided the Sub-profile, SLA profile, Ancp string and Intermediate Destination Id.

svcArpHostIfTableLastMgmtChange.name: svcArpHostIfTableLastMgmtChange
svcArpHostIfTableLastMgmtChange.description: The value of svcArpHostIfTableLastMgmtChange indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the most recent management-initiated change to the svcArpHostIfTable.

svcArpHostIfTable.name: svcArpHostIfTable
svcArpHostIfTable.description: A table that contains IES interface ARP host configuration information. A row is automatically created in the svcArpHostIfTable for an entry in the iesIfTable where either the value of the object iesIfType - is equal to 'group (3)' and the value of the object iesIfGroupInterfaceType is equal to 'plain' or 'lns', or - equal to 'subscriber (2)' while the value of the objects iesIfFwdServId and iesIfFwdSubIf are not equal to zero. The first case is referred to as 'group interface' and the second as 'retailer interface'.

svcArpHostIfEntry.name: svcArpHostIfEntry
svcArpHostIfEntry.description: ARP host specific information about an IES interface.

svcArpHostIfLastMgmtChange.name: svcArpHostIfLastMgmtChange
svcArpHostIfLastMgmtChange.description: The value of svcArpHostIfLastMgmtChange indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the most recent management-initiated change to this table row.

svcArpHostIfAdminState.name: svcArpHostIfAdminState
svcArpHostIfAdminState.description: The value of the object svcArpHostIfAdminState specifies the administrative state of the ARP host functionality on this IES interface. The default value of this object is equal to 'outOfService', except for a retailer interface, where it is 'inService'.

svcArpHostIfMaxNumHosts.name: svcArpHostIfMaxNumHosts
svcArpHostIfMaxNumHosts.description: The value of svcArpHostIfMaxNumHosts specifies the maximum number of ARP hosts allowed on this IES interface. The default value of this object is equal to '1' except for a retailer interface, where it is '32767'.

svcArpHostIfMaxNumHostsSap.name: svcArpHostIfMaxNumHostsSap
svcArpHostIfMaxNumHostsSap.description: The value of svcArpHostIfMaxNumHosts specifies the maximum number of ARP hosts per SAP allowed on this IES interface. The value of this object is not relevant in case of a retailer interface. In other cases, the default value is equal to '1'.

svcArpHostIfMinAuthInterval.name: svcArpHostIfMinAuthInterval
svcArpHostIfMinAuthInterval.description: The value of svcArpHostIfMinAuthInterval specifies the minimum interval between two consecutive authentication attempts for the same ARP host. The value of this object is not relevant in case of a retailer interface. In other cases, the default value is equal to '15'.

svcArpHostIfNumHosts.name: svcArpHostIfNumHosts
svcArpHostIfNumHosts.description: The value of svcArpHostIfNumHosts indicates the actual number of ARP hosts on this IES interface.

svcArpHostDefaultSessionTimeout.name: svcArpHostDefaultSessionTimeout
svcArpHostDefaultSessionTimeout.description: The value of svcArpHostDefaultSessionTimeout indicates the default value of the ARP host session timeout. This default value is used if no value was specified, for instance by the Radius server.

svcIgmpTrkTableLastMgmtChange.name: svcIgmpTrkTableLastMgmtChange
svcIgmpTrkTableLastMgmtChange.description: The value of svcIgmpTrkTableLastMgmtChange indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the most recent management-initiated change to the svcIgmpTrkTable.

svcIgmpTrkTable.name: svcIgmpTrkTable
svcIgmpTrkTable.description: A table that contains IGMP host tracking information of a service.

svcIgmpTrkEntry.name: svcIgmpTrkEntry
svcIgmpTrkEntry.description: IGMP host tracking information about a specific service.

svcIgmpTrkLastMgmtChange.name: svcIgmpTrkLastMgmtChange
svcIgmpTrkLastMgmtChange.description: The value of svcIgmpTrkLastMgmtChange indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the most recent management-initiated change to this table row.

svcIgmpTrkAdminState.name: svcIgmpTrkAdminState
svcIgmpTrkAdminState.description: The value of the object svcIgmpTrkAdminState specifies the administrative state of the IGMP host tracking in this service.

svcIgmpTrkExpiryTime.name: svcIgmpTrkExpiryTime
svcIgmpTrkExpiryTime.description: The value of the object svcIgmpTrkExpiryTime specifies the time in seconds that this system continues to track an inactive host.

svcIpipeInfoTableLastMgmtChange.name: svcIpipeInfoTableLastMgmtChange
svcIpipeInfoTableLastMgmtChange.description: The value of svcIpipeInfoTableLastMgmtChange indicates the timestamp of last change to the svcIpipeInfoTable.

svcIpipeInfoTable.name: svcIpipeInfoTable
svcIpipeInfoTable.description: A table that contains IPIPE service information.

svcIpipeInfoEntry.name: svcIpipeInfoEntry
svcIpipeInfoEntry.description: IPIPE specific information about a service.

svcIpipeInfoLastMgmtChange.name: svcIpipeInfoLastMgmtChange
svcIpipeInfoLastMgmtChange.description: The value of svcIpipeInfoLastMgmtChange indicates the value of sysUpTime at the time of the most recent management change to this row.

svcIpipeCeAddressDiscovery.name: svcIpipeCeAddressDiscovery
svcIpipeCeAddressDiscovery.description: The value of the object svcIpipeCeAddressDiscovery specifies whether the service will automatically discover the CE IP addresses. If 'enabled', the addresses will be automatically discovered on SAPs that support address discovery, and on the Spoke SDPs. When 'enabled', addresses configuration on the Ipipe SAP and Spoke SDPs will not be allowed. If 'disabled', CE IP addresses need to be manually configured for the SAPs to become operationally 'up'. svcIpipeCeAddressDiscovery cannot be disabled if svcIpipeIpv6CeAddressDiscovery is 'enabled'.

svcIpipeIpv6CeAddressDiscovery.name: svcIpipeIpv6CeAddressDiscovery
svcIpipeIpv6CeAddressDiscovery.description: The value of the object svcIpipeIpv6CeAddressDiscovery specifies whether the service will automatically discover the CE IPv6 addresses. If 'enabled', the addresses will be automatically discovered on SAPs that support address discovery, and on the Spoke SDPs. When 'enabled', addresses configuration on the Ipipe SAP and Spoke SDPs will not be allowed. If 'disabled', CE IP addresses need to be manually configured for the SAPs to become operationally 'up'. svcIpipeIpv6CeAddressDiscovery can only be enabled if svcIpipeCeAddressDiscovery is 'enabled' first.

svcIpipeStackCapabilitySignaling.name: svcIpipeStackCapabilitySignaling
svcIpipeStackCapabilitySignaling.description: The value of the object svcIpipeStackCapabilitySignaling specifies whether this service should send the Stack Capability or not, and check whether the capability is received from the peer via LDP interface parameters. If 'enabled' and svcIpipeIpv6CeAddressDiscovery is also 'enabled', the Stack Capability interface parameter will be sent via LDP to the far end peer. As well, if one is not received from the peer, the label for this service will be released. If 'disabled', the capability will not be advertised to the peer, and the presence or absence of this capability from the peer is ignored.

svcDhcpLeaseStateBgpTable.name: svcDhcpLeaseStateBgpTable
svcDhcpLeaseStateBgpTable.description: The svcDhcpLeaseStateBgpTable augments the svcDhcpLeaseStateTable. This table contains the parameters used for BGP.

svcDhcpLeaseStateBgpEntry.name: svcDhcpLeaseStateBgpEntry
svcDhcpLeaseStateBgpEntry.description: Each row entry contains parameters used for BGP.

svcDhcpLseStateBgpPrngPlcyName.name: svcDhcpLseStateBgpPrngPlcyName
svcDhcpLseStateBgpPrngPlcyName.description: The value of svcDhcpLseStateBgpPrngPlcyName indicates the peering policy which is used to set up the BGP peer for this lease state.

svcDhcpLseStateBgpAuthKeyChain.name: svcDhcpLseStateBgpAuthKeyChain
svcDhcpLseStateBgpAuthKeyChain.description: The value of svcDhcpLseStateBgpAuthKeyChain indicates the keychain which is used to sign and/or authenticate the BGP protocol stream.

svcDhcpLseStateBgpMD5AuthKey.name: svcDhcpLseStateBgpMD5AuthKey
svcDhcpLseStateBgpMD5AuthKey.description: The value of svcDhcpLseStateBgpMD5AuthKey indicates the authentication key used between BGP peers neighbors before establishing sessions. Authentication is done using the MD-5 message based digest protocol.

svcDhcpLseStateBgpImportPolicy.name: svcDhcpLseStateBgpImportPolicy
svcDhcpLseStateBgpImportPolicy.description: The value of svcDhcpLseStateBgpImportPolicy indicates the import policy.

svcDhcpLseStateBgpExportPolicy.name: svcDhcpLseStateBgpExportPolicy
svcDhcpLseStateBgpExportPolicy.description: The value of svcDhcpLseStateBgpExportPolicy indicates the export policy.

svcDhcpLseStateBgpPeerAS.name: svcDhcpLseStateBgpPeerAS
svcDhcpLseStateBgpPeerAS.description: The value of svcDhcpLseStateBgpPeerAS indicates the Autonomous System number for the remote peer.

svcDhcpLseStateBgpPeeringStatus.name: svcDhcpLseStateBgpPeeringStatus
svcDhcpLseStateBgpPeeringStatus.description: The value of svcDhcpLseStateBgpPeeringStatus indicates the status of the BGP peering session.

svcDhcpLeaseBgpTable.name: svcDhcpLeaseBgpTable
svcDhcpLeaseBgpTable.description: The svcDhcpLeaseBgpTable augments the svcDhcpLeaseTable. This table contains the parameters used for BGP.

svcDhcpLeaseBgpEntry.name: svcDhcpLeaseBgpEntry
svcDhcpLeaseBgpEntry.description: Each row entry contains parameters used for BGP.

svcDhcpLeaseBgpPrngPlcyName.name: svcDhcpLeaseBgpPrngPlcyName
svcDhcpLeaseBgpPrngPlcyName.description: The value of svcDhcpLeaseBgpPrngPlcyName indicates the peering policy which is used to set up the BGP peer for this lease state.

svcDhcpLeaseBgpAuthKeyChain.name: svcDhcpLeaseBgpAuthKeyChain
svcDhcpLeaseBgpAuthKeyChain.description: The value of svcDhcpLeaseBgpAuthKeyChain indicates the keychain which is used to sign and/or authenticate the BGP protocol stream.

svcDhcpLeaseBgpMD5AuthKey.name: svcDhcpLeaseBgpMD5AuthKey
svcDhcpLeaseBgpMD5AuthKey.description: The value of svcDhcpLeaseBgpMD5AuthKey indicates the authentication key used between BGP peers neighbors before establishing sessions. Authentication is done using the MD-5 message based digest protocol.

svcDhcpLeaseBgpImportPolicy.name: svcDhcpLeaseBgpImportPolicy
svcDhcpLeaseBgpImportPolicy.description: The value of svcDhcpLeaseBgpImportPolicy indicates the import policy.

svcDhcpLeaseBgpExportPolicy.name: svcDhcpLeaseBgpExportPolicy
svcDhcpLeaseBgpExportPolicy.description: The value of svcDhcpLeaseBgpExportPolicy indicates the export policy.

svcDhcpLeaseBgpPeerAS.name: svcDhcpLeaseBgpPeerAS
svcDhcpLeaseBgpPeerAS.description: The value of svcDhcpLeaseBgpPeerAS indicates the Autonomous System number for the remote peer.

svcDhcpLeaseBgpPeeringStatus.name: svcDhcpLeaseBgpPeeringStatus
svcDhcpLeaseBgpPeeringStatus.description: The value of svcDhcpLeaseBgpPeeringStatus indicates the status of the BGP peering session.

svcArpHostMRtTable.name: svcArpHostMRtTable
svcArpHostMRtTable.description: The svcArpHostMRtTable contains managed routes of ARP hosts. Entries in this table are created automatically by the system.

svcArpHostMRtEntry.name: svcArpHostMRtEntry
svcArpHostMRtEntry.description: Each row entry represents information on a specific managed route.

svcArpHostMRtAddrType.name: svcArpHostMRtAddrType
svcArpHostMRtAddrType.description: The value of svcArpHostMRtAddrType indicates the address type of svcArpHostMRtAddr.

svcArpHostMRtAddr.name: svcArpHostMRtAddr
svcArpHostMRtAddr.description: The value of svcArpHostMRtAddr indicates the IP address of the managed route.

svcArpHostMRtPrefixLen.name: svcArpHostMRtPrefixLen
svcArpHostMRtPrefixLen.description: The value of svcArpHostMRtPrefixLen indicates the prefix length of the subnet associated with svcArpHostMRtAddr.

svcArpHostMRtStatus.name: svcArpHostMRtStatus
svcArpHostMRtStatus.description: The value of svcArpHostMRtStatus indicates the state of this managed route.

svcArpHostBgpTable.name: svcArpHostBgpTable
svcArpHostBgpTable.description: The svcArpHostBgpTable augments the svcArpHostTable. This table contains the parameters used for BGP.

svcArpHostBgpEntry.name: svcArpHostBgpEntry
svcArpHostBgpEntry.description: Each row entry contains parameters used for BGP.

svcArpHostBgpPrngPlcyName.name: svcArpHostBgpPrngPlcyName
svcArpHostBgpPrngPlcyName.description: The value of svcArpHostBgpPrngPlcyName indicates the peering policy which is used to set up the BGP peer for this ARP host.

svcArpHostBgpAuthKeyChain.name: svcArpHostBgpAuthKeyChain
svcArpHostBgpAuthKeyChain.description: The value of svcArpHostBgpAuthKeyChain indicates the keychain which is used to sign and/or authenticate the BGP protocol stream.

svcArpHostBgpMD5AuthKey.name: svcArpHostBgpMD5AuthKey
svcArpHostBgpMD5AuthKey.description: The value of svcArpHostBgpMD5AuthKey indicates the authentication key used between BGP peers before establishing sessions. Authentication is done using the MD-5 message based digest protocol.

svcArpHostBgpImportPolicy.name: svcArpHostBgpImportPolicy
svcArpHostBgpImportPolicy.description: The value of svcArpHostBgpImportPolicy indicates the import policy.

svcArpHostBgpExportPolicy.name: svcArpHostBgpExportPolicy
svcArpHostBgpExportPolicy.description: The value of svcArpHostBgpExportPolicy indicates the export policy.

svcArpHostBgpPeerAS.name: svcArpHostBgpPeerAS
svcArpHostBgpPeerAS.description: The value of svcArpHostBgpPeerAS indicates the Autonomous System number for the remote peer.

svcArpHostBgpPeeringStatus.name: svcArpHostBgpPeeringStatus
svcArpHostBgpPeeringStatus.description: The value of svcArpHostBgpPeeringStatus indicates the status of the BGP peering session.

svcEpMcEpStatsTable.name: svcEpMcEpStatsTable
svcEpMcEpStatsTable.description: The svcEpMcEpStatsTable has an entry for each end-point that participates in a multi-chassis configuration for the indicated peer.

svcEpMcEpStatsEntry.name: svcEpMcEpStatsEntry
svcEpMcEpStatsEntry.description: Each row entry represents a collection of statistics for a end-point that participates in a multi-chassis configuration with a given peer. Entries cannot be created and deleted via SNMP SET operations.

svcEpMcEpStatsPktsRxConfig.name: svcEpMcEpStatsPktsRxConfig
svcEpMcEpStatsPktsRxConfig.description: The value of svcEpMcEpStatsPktsRxConfig indicates how many multi-chassis end-point control packets of type end-point config were received on this system from the peer for this end-point.

svcEpMcEpStatsPktsRxState.name: svcEpMcEpStatsPktsRxState
svcEpMcEpStatsPktsRxState.description: The value of svcEpMcEpStatsPktsRxState indicates how many multi-chassis end-point control packets of type end-point state were received on this system from the peer for this end-point.

svcEpMcEpStatsPktsTxConfig.name: svcEpMcEpStatsPktsTxConfig
svcEpMcEpStatsPktsTxConfig.description: The value of svcEpMcEpStatsPktsTxConfig indicates how many multi-chassis end-point control packets of type end-point config were sent on this system to the peer for this end-point.

svcEpMcEpStatsPktsTxState.name: svcEpMcEpStatsPktsTxState
svcEpMcEpStatsPktsTxState.description: The value of svcEpMcEpStatsPktsTxState indicates how many multi-chassis end-point control packets of type end-point state were sent on this system to the peer for this end-point.

svcEpMcEpStatsPktsTxFailed.name: svcEpMcEpStatsPktsTxFailed
svcEpMcEpStatsPktsTxFailed.description: The value of svcEpMcEpStatsPktsTxFailed indicates how many multi-chassis end-point control packets failed to be transmitted on this system to the peer for this end-point.

svcPbbSrcBVplsMacAddr.name: svcPbbSrcBVplsMacAddr
svcPbbSrcBVplsMacAddr.description: The value of svcPbbSrcBVplsMacAddr specifies the source Backbone MAC-Address to be used for Provider Backbone Bridging (PBB) packets. Value of default for this object indicates that chassis MAC address will be used for PBB packets.

svcMacNameTableLastChanged.name: svcMacNameTableLastChanged
svcMacNameTableLastChanged.description: The value of svcMacNameTableLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of svcMacNameTable. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcMacNameTable.name: svcMacNameTable
svcMacNameTable.description: The svcMacNameTable contains objects related to MAC-name feature. Entries are created and destroyed using svcMacNameRowStatus object.

svcMacNameEntry.name: svcMacNameEntry
svcMacNameEntry.description: Each row entry contains objects that allows the modification of the MAC-name objects.

svcMacName.name: svcMacName
svcMacName.description: The value of svcMacName specifies the name associated with a MAC address.

svcMacNameRowStatus.name: svcMacNameRowStatus
svcMacNameRowStatus.description: The value of svcMacNameRowStatus is used for the creation and deletion of MAC information. To create an entry in the table, svcMacNameAddr object must be set.

svcMacNameLastChngd.name: svcMacNameLastChngd
svcMacNameLastChngd.description: The value of svcMacNameLastChngd indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of this entry. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcMacNameAddr.name: svcMacNameAddr
svcMacNameAddr.description: The value of svcMacNameAddr specifies the MAC-Address associated with the name defined in svcMacName. This object must be set at the creation time.

tlsProtMacImplTable.name: tlsProtMacImplTable
tlsProtMacImplTable.description: A table that contains information about implicitly protected MAC addresses in a VPLS service.

tlsProtMacImplEntry.name: tlsProtMacImplEntry
tlsProtMacImplEntry.description: Each entry contains information about a specific implicitly protected MAC address. Rows are created or removed automatically by the system.

tlsProtMacImplMacAddr.name: tlsProtMacImplMacAddr
tlsProtMacImplMacAddr.description: The value of the object tlsProtMacImplMacAddr indicates the 48-bit IEEE 802.3 MAC address that is implicitly protected.

tlsProtMacImplLocale.name: tlsProtMacImplLocale
tlsProtMacImplLocale.description: The value of the object tlsProtMacImplLocale indicates where the protection of the MAC address defined by tlsProtMacImplMacAddr is applied: anywhere, or only on a specific SAP or SDP.

tlsProtMacImplPortId.name: tlsProtMacImplPortId
tlsProtMacImplPortId.description: When the value of tlsProtMacImplLocale is 'sap', this object, along with tlsProtMacImplEncapValue, indicates the SAP where this MAC address is protected. This object is otherwise insignificant and contains the value zero.

tlsProtMacImplEncapValue.name: tlsProtMacImplEncapValue
tlsProtMacImplEncapValue.description: The value of the object tlsProtMacImplEncapValue indicates, when the value of tlsProtMacImplLocale is 'sap', along with tlsProtMacImplPortId, the SAP where this MAC address is protected. This object is otherwise insignificant and contains the value zero.

tlsProtMacImplSdpBindId.name: tlsProtMacImplSdpBindId
tlsProtMacImplSdpBindId.description: The value of the object tlsProtMacImplSdpBindId indicates, when the value of tlsProtMacImplLocale is 'sdp', the SDP Binding where this MAC address is protected. This object is otherwise insignificant and contains the value zero.

tlsProtMacImplCount.name: tlsProtMacImplCount
tlsProtMacImplCount.description: The value of the object tlsProtMacImplCount indicates how many times the protection of this MAC was activated at the indicated locale since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, or the last time the system statistics were cleared.

svcMacNotifInterval.name: svcMacNotifInterval
svcMacNotifInterval.description: The value of svcMacNotifInterval specifies time-interval between subsequent MAC notification messages.

svcMacNotifCount.name: svcMacNotifCount
svcMacNotifCount.description: The value of svcMacNotifCount specifies number of MAC notification messages to be sent.

svcNameTableLastChanged.name: svcNameTableLastChanged
svcNameTableLastChanged.description: The value of svcNameTableLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of svcNameTable. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcNameTable.name: svcNameTable
svcNameTable.description: A table that contains basic service information. Entries can be created manually or automatically by the system when svcName object is set for the service.

svcNameEntry.name: svcNameEntry
svcNameEntry.description: Basic information about a specific service.

svcNameId.name: svcNameId
svcNameId.description: The value of the object svcNameId specifies the Service Identifier associated with this service. An 'inconsistentValue' error is returned if this object is set to default value when svcNameType is set to a non-default value or when this object is set to non-default value and svcNameType is set to default value.

svcNameRowStatus.name: svcNameRowStatus
svcNameRowStatus.description: This value of the object svcRowStatus specifies the status of this row.

svcNameLastChanged.name: svcNameLastChanged
svcNameLastChanged.description: The value of svcNameLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of this entry. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcNameType.name: svcNameType
svcNameType.description: The value of the object svcNameType specifies the service type: e.g. epipe, tls, etc. An 'inconsistentValue' error is returned if this object is set to default value when svcNameId is set to a non-default value or when this object is set to non-default value and svcNameId is set to default value.

svcMrpPlcyTableLastChgd.name: svcMrpPlcyTableLastChgd
svcMrpPlcyTableLastChgd.description: The value of svcMrpPlcyTableLastChgd indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of svcMrpPolicyTable. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcMrpPolicyTable.name: svcMrpPolicyTable
svcMrpPolicyTable.description: The svcMrpPolicyTable has an entry for each mrp-policy.

svcMrpPolicyEntry.name: svcMrpPolicyEntry
svcMrpPolicyEntry.description: svcMrpPolicyEntry contains the information about a particular mrp-policy.

svcMrpPolicyName.name: svcMrpPolicyName
svcMrpPolicyName.description: The value of svcMrpPolicyName specifies a specific mrp-policy.

svcMrpPolicyRowStatus.name: svcMrpPolicyRowStatus
svcMrpPolicyRowStatus.description: This value of the object svcMrpPolicyRowStatus specifies the status of this row.

svcMrpPolicyLastChanged.name: svcMrpPolicyLastChanged
svcMrpPolicyLastChanged.description: The value of svcMrpPolicyLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of this entry. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcMrpPolicyDescription.name: svcMrpPolicyDescription
svcMrpPolicyDescription.description: The value of svcMrpPolicyDescription specifies the user provided description of this mrp-policy.

svcMrpPolicyScope.name: svcMrpPolicyScope
svcMrpPolicyScope.description: The value of svcMrpPolicyScope specifies the scope of this mrp-policy definition. If defined as exclusive(1), this mrp-policy can be instantiated only once as compared to the multiple instances that the mrp-policy can have if defined as template(2).

svcMrpPolicyDefaultAction.name: svcMrpPolicyDefaultAction
svcMrpPolicyDefaultAction.description: The value of TMrpPolicyDefaultAction specifies the action to take for packets that do not match any mrp-policy entries.

svcMrpPlcyParamsTblLastChgd.name: svcMrpPlcyParamsTblLastChgd
svcMrpPlcyParamsTblLastChgd.description: The value of svcMrpPlcyParamsTblLastChgd indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of svcMrpPolicyParamsTable. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcMrpPolicyParamsTable.name: svcMrpPolicyParamsTable
svcMrpPolicyParamsTable.description: The svcMrpPolicyParamsTable has an entry for each mrp-policy entry.

svcMrpPolicyParamsEntry.name: svcMrpPolicyParamsEntry
svcMrpPolicyParamsEntry.description: svcMrpPolicyParamsEntry contains the information about a particular mrp-policy entry.

svcMrpPolicyParamsEntryId.name: svcMrpPolicyParamsEntryId
svcMrpPolicyParamsEntryId.description: The value of svcMrpPolicyParamsEntryId serves as a secondary index for each entry of a given mrp-policy.

svcMrpPolicyParamsRowStatus.name: svcMrpPolicyParamsRowStatus
svcMrpPolicyParamsRowStatus.description: This value of the object svcMrpPolicyParamsRowStatus specifies the status of this row.

svcMrpPolicyParamsLastChanged.name: svcMrpPolicyParamsLastChanged
svcMrpPolicyParamsLastChanged.description: The value of svcMrpPolicyParamsLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of this entry. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcMrpPolicyParamsDescription.name: svcMrpPolicyParamsDescription
svcMrpPolicyParamsDescription.description: The value of svcMrpPolicyParamsDescription specifies the user provided description of this mrp-policy entry.

svcMrpPolicyParamsAction.name: svcMrpPolicyParamsAction
svcMrpPolicyParamsAction.description: The value of svcMrpPolicyParamsAction specifies the action to take for packets that match this mrp-policy entry.

svcMrpPlcyParamsISIDTblLastChgd.name: svcMrpPlcyParamsISIDTblLastChgd
svcMrpPlcyParamsISIDTblLastChgd.description: The value of svcMrpPlcyParamsISIDTblLastChgd indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of svcMrpPolicyParamsISIDTable. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcMrpPolicyParamsISIDTable.name: svcMrpPolicyParamsISIDTable
svcMrpPolicyParamsISIDTable.description: The svcMrpPolicyParamsISIDTable has an entry for each ISID value/range in a particular mrp policy entry.

svcMrpPolicyParamsISIDEntry.name: svcMrpPolicyParamsISIDEntry
svcMrpPolicyParamsISIDEntry.description: svcMrpPolicyParamsISIDTable contains the information about an ISID value/range in a particular mrp-policy entry.

svcMrpPolicyParamsISIDLow.name: svcMrpPolicyParamsISIDLow
svcMrpPolicyParamsISIDLow.description: The value of svcMrpPolicyParamsISIDLow specifies the lowest value of the 24 bit (0..16777215) service instance identifier for this service that matches this entry and is used as third key of this MIB table. The value of this field can be equal to but not higher than the value of the svcMrpPolicyParamsISIDHigh field.

svcMrpPolicyParamsISIDHigh.name: svcMrpPolicyParamsISIDHigh
svcMrpPolicyParamsISIDHigh.description: The value of svcMrpPolicyParamsISIDHigh specifies the highest value of the 24 bit (0..16777215) service instance identifier for this service that matches this entry. The value of this field can be equal to but not lower than the value of the svcMrpPolicyParamsISIDLow field. If this field is modified in an existing row of this table, the new value will be silently rejected if it's lower than the existing value of svcMrpPolicyParamsISIDHigh.

svcMrpPolicyParamsISIDRowStatus.name: svcMrpPolicyParamsISIDRowStatus
svcMrpPolicyParamsISIDRowStatus.description: This value of the object svcMrpPolicyParamsISIDRowStatus specifies the status of this row.

svcMrpPolicyParamsISIDLastChgd.name: svcMrpPolicyParamsISIDLastChgd
svcMrpPolicyParamsISIDLastChgd.description: The value of svcMrpPolicyParamsISIDLastChgd indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of this entry. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcEpipeTableLastChanged.name: svcEpipeTableLastChanged
svcEpipeTableLastChanged.description: The value of svcEpipeTableLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of svcEpipeTable. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcEpipeTable.name: svcEpipeTable
svcEpipeTable.description: The svcEpipeTable contains objects related to 'epipe' services. Entries are created and destroyed when 'epipe' services are created and destroyed by the system.

svcEpipeEntry.name: svcEpipeEntry
svcEpipeEntry.description: Each row entry contains objects that allows the modification of the 'epipe' specific objects.

svcEpipeLastChngd.name: svcEpipeLastChngd
svcEpipeLastChngd.description: The value of svcEpipeLastChngd indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of this entry. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcEpipePerSvcHashing.name: svcEpipePerSvcHashing
svcEpipePerSvcHashing.description: The value of svcEpipePerSvcHashing specifies service-level hashing for Ethernet services.

svcEpipeBackboneTableLastChanged.name: svcEpipeBackboneTableLastChanged
svcEpipeBackboneTableLastChanged.description: The value of svcEpipeBackboneTableLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of svcEpipeBackboneTable. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcEpipeBackboneTable.name: svcEpipeBackboneTable
svcEpipeBackboneTable.description: The svcEpipeBackboneTable contains objects related to Provider Backbone Bridging (PBB) feature as relates to 'epipe' services. Entries are created and destroyed when 'epipe' services are created and destroyed by the system.

svcEpipeBackboneEntry.name: svcEpipeBackboneEntry
svcEpipeBackboneEntry.description: Each row entry contains objects that allows the modification of the PBB objects for an 'epipe' service.

svcEpipeBackboneLastChngd.name: svcEpipeBackboneLastChngd
svcEpipeBackboneLastChngd.description: The value of svcEpipeBackboneLastChngd indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of this entry. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcEpipeBackboneForceQTagFwd.name: svcEpipeBackboneForceQTagFwd
svcEpipeBackboneForceQTagFwd.description: The value of svcEpipeBackboneForceQTagFwd specifies whether to enable addition of an IEEE 802.1q tag after the Customer MAC address when the PBB header is built, as it egresses related 'b-vpls' service.

svcTlsSiteIdTblLastChanged.name: svcTlsSiteIdTblLastChanged
svcTlsSiteIdTblLastChanged.description: The value of svcTlsSiteIdTblLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of svcTlsSiteIdTable. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcTlsSiteIdTable.name: svcTlsSiteIdTable
svcTlsSiteIdTable.description: This table maintains the information about different sites defined in a service.

svcTlsSiteIdEntry.name: svcTlsSiteIdEntry
svcTlsSiteIdEntry.description: Information about a particular site in a specific service.

svcTlsSiteIdName.name: svcTlsSiteIdName
svcTlsSiteIdName.description: The value of svcTlsSiteIdName defines the name for the specific site.

svcTlsSiteIdRowStatus.name: svcTlsSiteIdRowStatus
svcTlsSiteIdRowStatus.description: The value of svcTlsSiteIdRowStatus is used for the creation and deletion of rows in this table.

svcTlsSiteIdLastChanged.name: svcTlsSiteIdLastChanged
svcTlsSiteIdLastChanged.description: The value of svcTlsSiteIdLastChanged indicates the timestamp of last change to this row in svcTlsSiteIdTable.

svcTlsSiteIdAdminStatus.name: svcTlsSiteIdAdminStatus
svcTlsSiteIdAdminStatus.description: The value of svcTlsSiteIdAdminStatus specifies the administrative state of the site instance associated with this service.

svcTlsSiteIdSiteId.name: svcTlsSiteIdSiteId
svcTlsSiteIdSiteId.description: The value of svcTlsSiteIdSiteId specifies the identifier for the site in this service. The value of svcTlsSiteIdSiteId is a two byte identifier usually employed for the BGP Multi-homing solution. It identifies the BGP Multi-homing site associated with one or a set of objects (SAPs, PWs or combination). The value of svcTlsSiteIdSiteId must be identical between the two PEs carrying the connection to the access device multi-homed to the PEs.

svcTlsSiteIdPortId.name: svcTlsSiteIdPortId
svcTlsSiteIdPortId.description: The value of svcTlsSiteIdPortId specifies the port associated with this site. The default value for this object indicates an invalid port. An 'inconsistentValue' error is returned when svcTlsSiteIdPortId is set to non-default and svcTlsSiteIdEncapValue is set to its default value or when svcTlsSiteIdPortId is set to its default value and svcTlsSiteIdEncapValue is set to non-default value. An 'inconsistentValue' error is returned if an attempt is made to set the non-default value to more than one of the following object groups (SAP, SDP-BIND, Split-Horizon Group name): SAP: svcTlsSiteIdPortId, svcTlsSiteIdEncapValue SDP-BIND: svcTlsSiteIdSdpBindId Split-Horizon Group name: svcTlsSiteIdShgName.

svcTlsSiteIdEncapValue.name: svcTlsSiteIdEncapValue
svcTlsSiteIdEncapValue.description: The value of svcTlsSiteIdEncapValue specifies the encap-value of the port associated with this site. An 'inconsistentValue' error is returned when svcTlsSiteIdPortId is set to non-default and svcTlsSiteIdEncapValue is set to its default value or when svcTlsSiteIdPortId is set to its default value and svcTlsSiteIdEncapValue is set to non-default value. An 'inconsistentValue' error is returned if an attempt is made to set the non-default value to more than one of the following object groups (SAP, SDP-BIND, Split-Horizon Group name): SAP: svcTlsSiteIdPortId, svcTlsSiteIdEncapValue SDP-BIND: svcTlsSiteIdSdpBindId Split-Horizon Group name: svcTlsSiteIdShgName.

svcTlsSiteIdSdpBindId.name: svcTlsSiteIdSdpBindId
svcTlsSiteIdSdpBindId.description: The value of the svcTlsSiteIdSdpBindId specifies the value of SDP binding associated with this site. An 'inconsistentValue' error is returned if an attempt is made to set the non-default value to more than one of the following object groups (SAP, SDP-BIND, Split-Horizon Group name): SAP: svcTlsSiteIdPortId, svcTlsSiteIdEncapValue SDP-BIND: svcTlsSiteIdSdpBindId Split-Horizon Group name: svcTlsSiteIdShgName.

svcTlsSiteIdShgName.name: svcTlsSiteIdShgName
svcTlsSiteIdShgName.description: The value of the svcTlsSiteIdShgName specifies the value of split-horizon group associated with this site. An 'inconsistentValue' error is returned if an attempt is made to set the non-default value to more than one of the following object groups (SAP, SDP-BIND, Split-Horizon Group name): SAP: svcTlsSiteIdPortId, svcTlsSiteIdEncapValue SDP-BIND: svcTlsSiteIdSdpBindId Split-Horizon Group name: svcTlsSiteIdShgName.

svcTlsSiteIdShgMeshSdp.name: svcTlsSiteIdShgMeshSdp
svcTlsSiteIdShgMeshSdp.description: The value of the svcTlsSiteIdShgMeshSdp specifies whether this site-id is to be applied to all the mesh-SDPs in this service.

svcTlsSiteIdFailedThresh.name: svcTlsSiteIdFailedThresh
svcTlsSiteIdFailedThresh.description: The value of the svcTlsSiteIdFailedThresh specifies the number of objects which are required to be in the 'down' state for this site to be declared in the 'down' state. The value of '-1' indicates that 'all' objects in this site should be down for the site to be declared in the 'down' state.

svcTlsSiteIdOperStatus.name: svcTlsSiteIdOperStatus
svcTlsSiteIdOperStatus.description: The value of the svcTlsSiteIdOperStatus indicates the operational status of the site.

svcTlsSiteIdDesignatedFwdr.name: svcTlsSiteIdDesignatedFwdr
svcTlsSiteIdDesignatedFwdr.description: The value of the svcTlsSiteIdDesignatedFwdr indicates whether this site has been declared as 'designated-forwarder' depending on the result of the BGP election.

svcTlsSiteIdBootTimer.name: svcTlsSiteIdBootTimer
svcTlsSiteIdBootTimer.description: The value of svcTlsSiteIdBootTimer specifies how long the system waits after a node reboot before running the DF (designated- forwarder) election algorithm. When this object is set to default value, system uses value of TIMETRA-MC-REDUNDANCY-MIB::tmnxMcRedBgpMultiHomeBootTimer object.

svcTlsSiteIdSiteActTimer.name: svcTlsSiteIdSiteActTimer
svcTlsSiteIdSiteActTimer.description: The value of svcTlsSiteIdSiteActTimer specifies the time-period the system keeps the local sites in standby status, waiting for BGP updates from remote PEs before running the DF (designated-forwarder) election algorithm to decide whether the site should be unblocked. When this object is set to default value, system uses value of TIMETRA-MC-REDUNDANCY-MIB::tmnxMcRedBgpMultiHomeSiteTimer object.

svcTlsSiteIdDfUpTime.name: svcTlsSiteIdDfUpTime
svcTlsSiteIdDfUpTime.description: The value of svcTlsSiteIdDfUpTime indicates the uptime of the designated forwarder for this site.

svcTlsSiteIdDfChgCnt.name: svcTlsSiteIdDfChgCnt
svcTlsSiteIdDfChgCnt.description: The value of svcTlsSiteIdDfChgCnt indicates the number of times designated forwarder has changed.

svcTlsSiteIdTimerRemain.name: svcTlsSiteIdTimerRemain
svcTlsSiteIdTimerRemain.description: The value of svcTlsSiteIdTimerRemain indicates remaining time in the timer for this site.

svcTlsSiteIdMonitorOperGrp.name: svcTlsSiteIdMonitorOperGrp
svcTlsSiteIdMonitorOperGrp.description: The value of the svcTlsSiteIdMonitorOperGrp specifies the Operational-Group identifier which will affect the state of this site.

svcBgpVplsTblLastChanged.name: svcBgpVplsTblLastChanged
svcBgpVplsTblLastChanged.description: The value of svcBgpVplsTblLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of svcBgpVplsTable. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcBgpVplsTable.name: svcBgpVplsTable
svcBgpVplsTable.description: This table maintains the information about BGP-VPLS feature information for a service.

svcBgpVplsEntry.name: svcBgpVplsEntry
svcBgpVplsEntry.description: Information about BGP-VPLS feature for a specific service.

svcBgpVplsRowStatus.name: svcBgpVplsRowStatus
svcBgpVplsRowStatus.description: The value of svcBgpVplsRowStatus is used for the creation and deletion of rows in this table.

svcBgpVplsLastChanged.name: svcBgpVplsLastChanged
svcBgpVplsLastChanged.description: The value of svcBgpVplsLastChanged indicates the timestamp of last change to this row in svcBgpVplsTable.

svcBgpVplsMaxVeId.name: svcBgpVplsMaxVeId
svcBgpVplsMaxVeId.description: The value of the svcBgpVplsMaxVeId specifies the value of vpls-edge-range for this service.

svcBgpVplsAdminStatus.name: svcBgpVplsAdminStatus
svcBgpVplsAdminStatus.description: The value of svcBgpVplsAdminStatus specifies the administrative state of the vpls-edge instance associated with this service.

svcBgpVplsVeName.name: svcBgpVplsVeName
svcBgpVplsVeName.description: The value of svcBgpVplsVeName specifies the name for the specific vpls-edge.

svcBgpVplsVeId.name: svcBgpVplsVeId
svcBgpVplsVeId.description: The value of svcBgpVplsVeId specifies the identifier for the vpls-edge in this service. The svcBgpVplsVeId is a two bytes identifier that represents the local bridging instance in a VPLS and is advertised through the BGP Network Layer Reachability Information (NLRI). An 'inconsistentValue' error is returned if value of svcBgpVplsVeId is set to the value of svcBgpVplsMaxVeId or lower. An 'inconsistentError' is returned if this object is set to non-default value when svcBgpVplsVeName is set to its default value.

svcTlsBgpTableLastChanged.name: svcTlsBgpTableLastChanged
svcTlsBgpTableLastChanged.description: The value of svcTlsBgpTableLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of svcTlsBgpTable. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcTlsBgpTable.name: svcTlsBgpTable
svcTlsBgpTable.description: svcTlsBgpTable contains entries for BGP in a VPLS service context.

svcTlsBgpEntry.name: svcTlsBgpEntry
svcTlsBgpEntry.description: A BGP entry in the svcTlsBgpTable.

svcTlsBgpLastChanged.name: svcTlsBgpLastChanged
svcTlsBgpLastChanged.description: The value of svcTlsBgpLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of this entry. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcTlsBgpVsiRD.name: svcTlsBgpVsiRD
svcTlsBgpVsiRD.description: The value of svcTlsBgpVsiRD specifies the high-order 6 bytes used to compose the Virtual Switch Instance identifier (VSI-id) to use for NLRI in BGP in this VPLS service. If the value of svcTlsBgpVsiRD is 0x0000000000000000, the lower 6 bytes of the VPLS-id, as specified by svcTlsBgpADVplsId, will be used.

svcTlsBgpExportRteTarget.name: svcTlsBgpExportRteTarget
svcTlsBgpExportRteTarget.description: The value of svcTlsBgpExportRteTarget specifies the extended community name for the default export policy to use for BGP in this VPLS service. This object cannot be set to a non-empty if svcTlsBgpExportRteTarget has a non-empty value, otherwise an 'inconsistentValue' error will be returned.

svcTlsBgpVsiExportPolicy1.name: svcTlsBgpVsiExportPolicy1
svcTlsBgpVsiExportPolicy1.description: The value of svcTlsBgpVsiExportPolicy1 specifies the name of the first VSI export policy to be used for BGP in this VPLS service. If multiple policy names are specified, the policies are evaluated in the order they are specified. The first policy that matches is applied. The import policy name list, svcTlsBgpVsiExportPolicy1 through svcTlsBgpVsiExportPolicy5, is handled by the SNMP agent as a single entity. When an SNMP SET request is received to modify one or more of the policy names, all the policy variables are first set to the empty string, ''H, and then the new names are set into the specified policy variables within a single SNMP SET PDU.

svcTlsBgpVsiExportPolicy2.name: svcTlsBgpVsiExportPolicy2
svcTlsBgpVsiExportPolicy2.description: The value of svcTlsBgpVsiExportPolicy2 specifies the name of the second VSI export policy to be used for BGP in this VPLS service. If multiple policy names are specified, the policies are evaluated in the order they are specified. The first policy that matches is applied. The import policy name list, svcTlsBgpVsiExportPolicy1 through svcTlsBgpVsiExportPolicy5, is handled by the SNMP agent as a single entity. When an SNMP SET request is received to modify one or more of the policy names, all the policy variables are first set to the empty string, ''H, and then the new names are set into the specified policy variables within a single SNMP SET PDU.

svcTlsBgpVsiExportPolicy3.name: svcTlsBgpVsiExportPolicy3
svcTlsBgpVsiExportPolicy3.description: The value of svcTlsBgpVsiExportPolicy3 specifies the name of the third VSI export policy to be used for BGP in this VPLS service. If multiple policy names are specified, the policies are evaluated in the order they are specified. The first policy that matches is applied. svcTlsBgpImportRteTarget.description: The value of svcTlsBgpImportRteTarget specifies the extended community name for the default import policy to use for BGP in this VPLS service. This object cannot be set to a non-empty if svcTlsBgpImportRteTarget has a non-empty value, otherwise an 'inconsistentValue' error will be returned.

svcTlsBgpVsiImportPolicy1.description: The value of svcTlsBgpVsiImportPolicy1 specifies the name of the first VSI export policy to be used for BGP in this VPLS service. svcTlsBgpRowStatus.name: svcTlsBgpRowStatus
svcTlsBgpRowStatus.description: The value of svcTlsBgpRowStatus is used for the creation and deletion of rows in this table.

svcTlsPbbIgmpSnpgMRtrTable.name: svcTlsPbbIgmpSnpgMRtrTable
svcTlsPbbIgmpSnpgMRtrTable.description: A table that contains Provider Backbone Bridging (PBB/IEEE 802.1ah) IGMP Snooping MRouter Destination information.

svcTlsPbbIgmpSnpgMRtrEntry.name: svcTlsPbbIgmpSnpgMRtrEntry
svcTlsPbbIgmpSnpgMRtrEntry.description: PBB I-Component instance-specific information about a specific IGMP Snooping MRouter in the B-Component instance. Entries in this table can be created or deleted via SNMP operations.

svcTlsPbbIgmpSnpgMRtrSvcIdIVpls.name: svcTlsPbbIgmpSnpgMRtrSvcIdIVpls
svcTlsPbbIgmpSnpgMRtrSvcIdIVpls.description: The value of the object svcTlsPbbIgmpSnpgMRtrSvcIdIVpls specifies the Service identifier of the I-Component instance.

svcTlsPbbIgmpSnpgMRtrSvcIdBVpls.name: svcTlsPbbIgmpSnpgMRtrSvcIdBVpls
svcTlsPbbIgmpSnpgMRtrSvcIdBVpls.description: The value of the object svcTlsPbbIgmpSnpgMRtrSvcIdBVpls specifies the Service identifier of the B-Component instance.

svcTlsPbbIgmpSnpgMRtrMacName.name: svcTlsPbbIgmpSnpgMRtrMacName
svcTlsPbbIgmpSnpgMRtrMacName.description: The value of svcTlsPbbIgmpSnpgMRtrMacName specifies the Destination MAC-Address-Name in the Backbone VPLS to reach a specific IGMP Snooping MRouter. In the case of an I-Component instance that is multi-homed on 2 physical nodes, an I-component instance, after becoming active, uses this MAC address as the destination MAC address to reach that IGMP Snooping MRouter. This allows to maintain the communication with that MRouter while no IGMP Queries from that MRouter have been snooped by this I-component instance.

svcTlsPbbIgmpSnpgMRtrRowStatus.name: svcTlsPbbIgmpSnpgMRtrRowStatus
svcTlsPbbIgmpSnpgMRtrRowStatus.description: The value of svcTlsPbbIgmpSnpgMRtrRowStatus specifies the row status of this row. The only values supported during a set operation are 'createAndGo' and 'destroy'.

svcTlsPbbIgmpSnpgMRtrLastCh.name: svcTlsPbbIgmpSnpgMRtrLastCh
svcTlsPbbIgmpSnpgMRtrLastCh.description: The value of svcTlsPbbIgmpSnpgMRtrLastCh indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the most recent management-initiated change to this table row.

svcL2MhRteTable.name: svcL2MhRteTable
svcL2MhRteTable.description: svcL2MhRteTable contains multi-home entries for L2 routes.

svcL2MhRteEntry.name: svcL2MhRteEntry
svcL2MhRteEntry.description: A multi-home L2 route entry in the svcL2MhRteTable.

svcL2MhRteSiteId.name: svcL2MhRteSiteId
svcL2MhRteSiteId.description: The value of svcL2MhRteSiteId is the site-id for this L2 route.

svcL2MhRteRouteDistinguisher.name: svcL2MhRteRouteDistinguisher
svcL2MhRteRouteDistinguisher.description: The value of svcL2MhRteRouteDistinguisher is the high-order 6 bytes of the Virtual Switch Instance identifier (VSI-id) of the remote VSI for this L2 route.

svcL2MhRteNextHopType.name: svcL2MhRteNextHopType
svcL2MhRteNextHopType.description: The value of svcL2MhRteNextHopType indicates the address type of svcL2MhRteNextHop.

svcL2MhRteNextHop.name: svcL2MhRteNextHop
svcL2MhRteNextHop.description: The value of svcL2MhRteNextHop indicates the IP next hop for this L2 route. This value is equivilant to the IP address of the Far End of this L2 route.

svcL2MhRteState.name: svcL2MhRteState
svcL2MhRteState.description: The value of svcL2MhRteState indicates the state of this multi-home L2 route entry.

svcL2MhRteDf.name: svcL2MhRteDf
svcL2MhRteDf.description: The value of svcL2MhRteDf indicates the value of DF bit associated with this multi-home L2 route entry.

svcTmplTblLastChanged.name: svcTmplTblLastChanged
svcTmplTblLastChanged.description: The value of svcTmplTblLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of svcTmplTable. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcTmplTable.name: svcTmplTable
svcTmplTable.description: A table that contains basic service template information.

svcTmplEntry.name: svcTmplEntry
svcTmplEntry.description: Basic information about a specific service template.

svcTmplName.name: svcTmplName
svcTmplName.description: The value of the svcTmplName specifies the Service template name. This name should unique within the service template domain.

svcTmplRowStatus.name: svcTmplRowStatus
svcTmplRowStatus.description: This value of the object svcTmplRowStatus specifies the status of this row.

svcTmplLastChanged.name: svcTmplLastChanged
svcTmplLastChanged.description: The value of svcTmplLastChanged indicates the timestamp of last change to this row in svcTmplTable.

svcTmplSvcCount.name: svcTmplSvcCount
svcTmplSvcCount.description: The value of svcTmplSvcCount indicates the number of instantiated services created using this template.

svcTmplType.name: svcTmplType
svcTmplType.description: The value of the object svcTmplType specifies the service type: e.g. epipe, tls, etc. The value of this object must be specified when the row is created and cannot be changed while the row status is 'active'. An 'inconsistentValue' error is returned if an attempt is made to change the value of this object after row creation.

svcTmplMtu.name: svcTmplMtu
svcTmplMtu.description: The value of the object svcTmplMtu specifies the largest frame size (in octets) that this service can handle. The default value of this object depends on the service type: 1514 octets for epipe, p3pipe and tls, 1508 for apipe and fpipe, and 1500 octets for vprn, ipipe and ies, 1514 octets for cpipe.

svcTmplCustId.name: svcTmplCustId
svcTmplCustId.description: The value of the object svcTmplCustId specifies the customer identifier of the service.

svcTmplTlsTblLastChanged.name: svcTmplTlsTblLastChanged
svcTmplTlsTblLastChanged.description: The value of svcTmplTlsTblLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of svcTmplTlsTable. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcTmplTlsTable.name: svcTmplTlsTable
svcTmplTlsTable.description: A table that contains VPLS service template information.

svcTmplTlsEntry.name: svcTmplTlsEntry
svcTmplTlsEntry.description: This table contains basic information about a specific VPLS service template. An entry in this table is created when an entry is created in the svcTmplTable with svcTmplType set to 'tls'. Entry is deleted when corrosponding entry is deleted in the svcTmplTable.

svcTmplTlsLastChanged.name: svcTmplTlsLastChanged
svcTmplTlsLastChanged.description: The value of svcTmplTlsLastChanged indicates the timestamp of last change to this row in svcTmplTlsTable.

svcTmplTlsMacLearning.name: svcTmplTlsMacLearning
svcTmplTlsMacLearning.description: The value of the object svcTmplTlsMacLearning specifies whether the MAC learning process is enabled in this TLS.

svcTmplTlsDiscardUnknownDest.name: svcTmplTlsDiscardUnknownDest
svcTmplTlsDiscardUnknownDest.description: The value of the object svcTmplTlsDiscardUnknownDest specifies whether frames received with an unknown destination MAC are discarded in this TLS.

svcTmplTlsFdbTableSize.name: svcTmplTlsFdbTableSize
svcTmplTlsFdbTableSize.description: The value of svcTmplTlsFdbTableSize specifies the maximum number of learned and static entries allowed in the FDB of this service.

svcTmplTlsFdbLocalAgeTime.name: svcTmplTlsFdbLocalAgeTime
svcTmplTlsFdbLocalAgeTime.description: The value of the object svcTmplTlsFdbLocalAgeTime specifies the number of seconds used to age out TLS FDB entries learned on local SAPs.

svcTmplTlsFdbRemoteAgeTime.name: svcTmplTlsFdbRemoteAgeTime
svcTmplTlsFdbRemoteAgeTime.description: The value of svcTmplTlsFdbRemoteAgeTime specifies the number of seconds used to age out TLS FDB entries learned on an SDP. These entries correspond to MAC addresses learned on remote SAPs.

svcTmplTlsStpAdminStatus.name: svcTmplTlsStpAdminStatus
svcTmplTlsStpAdminStatus.description: The value of svcTmplTlsStpAdminStatus specifies the administrative state of the Spanning Tree Protocol instance associated with this service.

svcTmplTlsStpPriority.name: svcTmplTlsStpPriority
svcTmplTlsStpPriority.description: The value of svcTmplTlsStpPriority specifies the priority of the Spanning Tree Protocol instance associated with this service. It is used as the highest 4 bits of the Bridge ID included in the Configuration BPDU's generated by this bridge. The svcTmplTlsStpPriority can only take-on values which multiples of 4096 (4k). If a value is specified which is not a multiple of 4K, then this value will be replaced by the closest multiple of 4K which is lower then the value entered.

svcTmplTlsStpBridgeMaxAge.name: svcTmplTlsStpBridgeMaxAge
svcTmplTlsStpBridgeMaxAge.description: The value of svcTmplTlsStpBridgeMaxAge specifies the value that all bridges should use for 'MaxAge' when this bridge is acting as the root bridge.

svcTmplTlsStpBridgeHelloTime.name: svcTmplTlsStpBridgeHelloTime
svcTmplTlsStpBridgeHelloTime.description: The value of svcTmplTlsStpBridgeHelloTime specifies the value that all bridges should use for 'HelloTime' when this bridge is acting as the root bridge.

svcTmplTlsStpBridgeForwardDelay.name: svcTmplTlsStpBridgeForwardDelay
svcTmplTlsStpBridgeForwardDelay.description: The value of svcTmplTlsStpBridgeForwardDelay specifies the value that all bridges should use for 'ForwardDelay' when this bridge is acting as the root bridge.

svcTmplTlsMacAgeing.name: svcTmplTlsMacAgeing
svcTmplTlsMacAgeing.description: The value of svcTmplTlsMacAgeing specifies whether the MAC aging process is enabled in this TLS.

svcTmplTlsFdbTableFullHighWMark.name: svcTmplTlsFdbTableFullHighWMark
svcTmplTlsFdbTableFullHighWMark.description: The value of svcTmplTlsFdbTableFullHighWMark specifies the utilization of the FDB table of this TLS service at which a table full alarm will be raised by the agent.

svcTmplTlsFdbTableFullLowWMark.name: svcTmplTlsFdbTableFullLowWMark
svcTmplTlsFdbTableFullLowWMark.description: The value of svcTmplTlsFdbTableFullLowWMark specifies the utilization of the FDB table of this TLS service at which a table full alarm will be cleared by the agent.

svcTmplTlsStpVersion.name: svcTmplTlsStpVersion
svcTmplTlsStpVersion.description: The value of svcTmplTlsStpVersion specifies the version of Spanning Tree Protocol the bridge is currently running. The value 'rstp' corresponds to the Rapid Spanning Tree Protocol specified in IEEE 802.1D/D4-2003. The value 'compDot1w' corresponds to the mode where the Rapid Spanning Tree is backward compatible with IEEE 802.1w. The value 'dot1w' corresponds to the Rapid Spanning Tree Protocol fully conformant to IEEE 802.1w. The value 'mstp' corresponds to the Multiple Spanning Tree Protocol specified in IEEE 802.1Q-REV/D3.0-04/2005. The value 'pmstp' corresponds to Provider MSTP protocol compliant with IEEE-802.1ad-2005. New values may be defined as future versions of the protocol become available.

svcTmplTlsStpHoldCount.name: svcTmplTlsStpHoldCount
svcTmplTlsStpHoldCount.description: The value of svcTmplTlsStpHoldCount specifies the maximum number of BPDUs that are transmitted in any 'HelloTime' interval. The value used by the bridge to limit the maximum transmission rate of BPDUs.

svcTmplTlsPerSvcHashing.name: svcTmplTlsPerSvcHashing
svcTmplTlsPerSvcHashing.description: The value of svcTmplTlsPerSvcHashing specifies service-level hashing for Ethernet services. An 'inconsistentValue' error is returned if this object is set to non-default value when svcVplsType for the service is set to 'bVpls'.

svcTmplTlsTempFloodTime.name: svcTmplTlsTempFloodTime
svcTmplTlsTempFloodTime.description: The value of svcTmplTlsTempFloodTime specifies duration of time traffic will be flooded on a TLS status change in this TLS. Value of '-1' disables this flooding behavior.

svcTmplTlsMacMoveMaxRate.name: svcTmplTlsMacMoveMaxRate
svcTmplTlsMacMoveMaxRate.description: The value of svcTmplTlsMacMoveMaxRate specifies the maximum rate at which MAC's can be re-learned in this TLS service, before the SAP where the moving MAC was last seen is automatically disabled in order to protect the system against undetected loops or duplicate MAC's. The rate is computed as the maximum number of re-learns allowed in a 5 second interval: e.g. the default rate of 2 re-learns per second corresponds to 10 re-learns in a 5 second period.

svcTmplTlsMacMoveRetryTimeout.name: svcTmplTlsMacMoveRetryTimeout
svcTmplTlsMacMoveRetryTimeout.description: The value of svcTmplTlsMacMoveRetryTimeout specifies the time in seconds to wait before a SAP that has been disabled after exceeding the maximum re-learn rate is re-enabled. A value of zero indicates that the SAP will not be automatically re-enabled after being disabled. If after the SAP is re-enabled it is disabled again, the effective retry timeout is doubled in order to avoid thrashing. An inconsistentValue error is returned if the value of this object is set to less than fie times the value of svcTmplTlsSecPortsCumFactor.

svcTmplTlsMacMoveAdminStatus.name: svcTmplTlsMacMoveAdminStatus
svcTmplTlsMacMoveAdminStatus.description: The value of svcTmplTlsMacMoveAdminStatus specifies the administrative state of the MAC movement feature associated with this service.

svcTmplTlsPriPortsCumFactor.name: svcTmplTlsPriPortsCumFactor
svcTmplTlsPriPortsCumFactor.description: The value of svcTmplTlsPriPortsCumFactor specifies a factor for the primary ports defining how many MAC-relearn periods should be used to measure the MAC-relearn rate, svcTmplTlsMacMoveMaxRate. This rate must be exceeded during consecutive periods before the corresponding ports (SAP and/or spoke-SDP) are blocked by the MAC-move feature. An inconsistentValue error is returned if an attempt is made to set the value of svcTmplTlsPriPortsCumFactor to a value lower than or equal to svcTmplTlsSecPortsCumFactor.

svcTmplTlsSecPortsCumFactor.name: svcTmplTlsSecPortsCumFactor
svcTmplTlsSecPortsCumFactor.description: The value of svcTmplTlsSecPortsCumFactor specifies a factor for the secondary ports defining how many MAC-relearn periods should be used to measure the MAC-relearn rate, svcTmplTlsMacMoveMaxRate. This rate must be exceeded during consecutive periods before the corresponding ports (SAP and/or spoke-SDP) are blocked by the MAC-move feature. An inconsistentValue error is returned if an attempt is made to set the value of svcTmplTlsSecPortsCumFactor to a value greater than or equal to svcTmplTlsPriPortsCumFactor.

svcTmplTlsMacMoveNumRetries.name: svcTmplTlsMacMoveNumRetries
