svcTmplTlsMacMoveNumRetries.description: The value of svcTmplTlsMacMoveNumRetries specifies the number of times retries are performed for reenabling the SAP/SDP. A value of zero indicates unlimited number of retries.

svcTlsGroupTblLastChanged.name: svcTlsGroupTblLastChanged
svcTlsGroupTblLastChanged.description: The value of svcTlsGroupTblLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of svcTlsGroupTable. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcTlsGroupTable.name: svcTlsGroupTable
svcTlsGroupTable.description: A table that contains TLS service range information for the service.

svcTlsGroupEntry.name: svcTlsGroupEntry
svcTlsGroupEntry.description: TLS service range specific information for this service.

svcTlsGroupId.name: svcTlsGroupId
svcTlsGroupId.description: The value of the object svcTlsGroupId specifies the Service range identifier under this service.

svcTlsGroupRowStatus.name: svcTlsGroupRowStatus
svcTlsGroupRowStatus.description: This value of the object svcTlsGroupRowStatus specifies the status of this row.

svcTlsGroupLastChanged.name: svcTlsGroupLastChanged
svcTlsGroupLastChanged.description: The value of svcTlsGroupLastChanged indicates the timestamp of last change to this row in svcTlsGroupTable.

svcTlsGroupAdminStatus.name: svcTlsGroupAdminStatus
svcTlsGroupAdminStatus.description: The value of svcTlsGroupAdminStatus specifies the desired state of this service-range.

svcTlsGroupStart.name: svcTlsGroupStart
svcTlsGroupStart.description: The value of the object svcTlsGroupStart specifies the start of the service identifier range. An 'inconsistentValue' error is returned when the value of svcTlsGroupStart is set to larger than the value of svcTlsGroupEnd. An 'inconsistentValue' error is also returned when the value of svcTlsGroupStart is set to default and svcTlsGroupStartVlanTag is set to non-default value. An 'inconsistentValue' error is also returned when the value of svcTlsGroupEnd is set to non-default value and svcTlsGroupStart is set to the default value.

svcTlsGroupEnd.name: svcTlsGroupEnd
svcTlsGroupEnd.description: The value of the object svcTlsGroupEnd specifies the end of the service identifier range. An 'inconsistentValue' error is returned when the value of svcTlsGroupStart is set to larger than the value of svcTlsGroupEnd. An 'inconsistentValue' error is also returned when the value of svcTlsGroupEnd is set to non-default value and svcTlsGroupStart is set to the default value.

svcTlsGroupStartVlanTag.name: svcTlsGroupStartVlanTag
svcTlsGroupStartVlanTag.description: The value of the object svcTlsGroupStartVlanTag specifies the start of the VLAN tag range. An 'inconsistentValue' error is also returned when the value of svcTlsGroupStart is set to default and svcTlsGroupStartVlanTag is set to non-default value.

svcTlsGroupSvcTmplName.name: svcTlsGroupSvcTmplName
svcTlsGroupSvcTmplName.description: The value of the object svcTlsGroupSvcTmplName specifies the service template name associated with this service-range.

svcTlsGroupSapTmplName.name: svcTlsGroupSapTmplName
svcTlsGroupSapTmplName.description: The value of the object svcTlsGroupSapTmplName specifies the SAP template name associated with this service-range.

svcTlsGroupMvrpControl.name: svcTlsGroupMvrpControl
svcTlsGroupMvrpControl.description: The value of the object svcTlsGroupMvrpControl specifies whether MVRP control is enabled on this service-range.

svcTlsGroupOperStatus.name: svcTlsGroupOperStatus
svcTlsGroupOperStatus.description: The value of svcTlsGroupOperStatus indicates service instantiation status of this service group. A value of 'down' indicates: -- svcTmplGroupAdminStatus is set to 'disabled' or -- services for this group are being instantiated or -- service instantiation failed for this group. svcTlsGroupLastError provide information on the error encountered. A value of 'up' indicates that all services for this group have been successfully instantiated. A value of 'inProgress' indicates that this group is in process of transitioning to another state.

svcTlsGroupLastError.name: svcTlsGroupLastError
svcTlsGroupLastError.description: The value of the object svcTlsGroupLastError indicates the last error encountered trying to instantiate services for this group.

svcTmplUserTable.name: svcTmplUserTable
svcTmplUserTable.description: A table that contains services which are created using Service templates.

svcTmplUserEntry.name: svcTmplUserEntry
svcTmplUserEntry.description: This table provides information about services created using a service template. Entries are created and deleted by the system.

svcTmplUserCreationOrigin.name: svcTmplUserCreationOrigin
svcTmplUserCreationOrigin.description: The value svcTmplUserCreationOrigin indicates how the service was created using this specific service template.

svcTmplUserCreatorSvcId.name: svcTmplUserCreatorSvcId
svcTmplUserCreatorSvcId.description: The value svcTmplUserCreatorSvcId indicates the service identifier which created this particular service using this template. A value of zero indicates that the service is not created by another service.

svcTlsExtMvrpMaxAttributes.name: svcTlsExtMvrpMaxAttributes
svcTlsExtMvrpMaxAttributes.description: The value of the object svcTlsExtMvrpMaxAttributes indicates maximum number of MVRP attributes supported in this TLS. An 'inconsitentValue' error is returned if this object is set to non-default value when svcMgmtVpls of the service is not set to 'true'.

svcTlsExtMvrpRegAttrCnt.name: svcTlsExtMvrpRegAttrCnt
svcTlsExtMvrpRegAttrCnt.description: The value of the object svcTlsExtMvrpRegAttrCnt indicates the number of MVRP attributes currently associated to the TLS by being registered.

svcTlsExtMvrpDeclaredAttrCnt.name: svcTlsExtMvrpDeclaredAttrCnt
svcTlsExtMvrpDeclaredAttrCnt.description: The value of the object svcTlsExtMvrpDeclaredAttrCnt indicates the number of MVRP attributes currently associated to the TLS by being declared.

svcTlsExtMvrpFailedRegCnt.name: svcTlsExtMvrpFailedRegCnt
svcTlsExtMvrpFailedRegCnt.description: The value of the object svcTlsExtMvrpFailedRegCnt indicates number of failed MVRP attribute registrations in this TLS.

svcTlsExtMvrpAttrTblHighWM.name: svcTlsExtMvrpAttrTblHighWM
svcTlsExtMvrpAttrTblHighWM.description: The value of the object svcTlsExtMvrpAttrTblHighWM specifies the utilization of the MVRP attribute table of this TLS service at which a table full alarm will be raised by the agent. An 'inconsitentValue' error is returned if this object is set to non-default value when svcMgmtVpls of the service is not set to 'true'.

svcTlsExtMvrpAttrTblLowWM.name: svcTlsExtMvrpAttrTblLowWM
svcTlsExtMvrpAttrTblLowWM.description: The value of the object svcTlsExtMvrpAttrTblLowWM specifies utilization of the MVRP attribute table of this TLS service at which a table full alarm will be cleared by the agent. An 'inconsitentValue' error is returned if this object is set to non-default value when svcMgmtVpls of the service is not set to 'true'.

svcTlsExtMvrpHoldTime.name: svcTlsExtMvrpHoldTime
svcTlsExtMvrpHoldTime.description: The value of the object svcTlsExtMvrpHoldTime specifies the amount of time in minutes in reporting to MVRP that the last provisioned SAP in VPLS is down. A value of '0' disables tracking of the operational status for the last active SAP in the VPLS. An 'inconsitentValue' error is returned if this object is set to non-default value when svcMgmtVpls of the service is not set to 'true'.

svcTlsExtMvrpAdminStatus.name: svcTlsExtMvrpAdminStatus
svcTlsExtMvrpAdminStatus.description: The value of the object svcTlsExtMvrpAdminStatus specifies whether the Multiple VLAN Registration Protocol (MVRP) is enabled in this TLS. An 'inconsitentValue' error is returned if this object is set to non-default value when svcMgmtVpls of the service is not set to 'true'.

svcTlsExtMvrpOperStatus.name: svcTlsExtMvrpOperStatus
svcTlsExtMvrpOperStatus.description: The value of the object svcTlsExtMvrpOperStatus indicates the operational status of Multiple VLAN Registration Protocol (MVRP) in this TLS.

svcTlsExtMmrpAdminStatus.name: svcTlsExtMmrpAdminStatus
svcTlsExtMmrpAdminStatus.description: The value of the object svcTlsExtMmrpAdminStatus specifies whether the Multiple MAC Registration Protocol (MMRP) is enabled in this TLS. Default value of this object is set to 'enabled' when svcVplsType of this service is set to 'bVpls' otherwise this is set to 'disabled'.

svcTlsExtMmrpOperStatus.name: svcTlsExtMmrpOperStatus
svcTlsExtMmrpOperStatus.description: The value of the object svcTlsExtMmrpOperStatus indicates the operational status of Multiple MAC Registration Protocol (MMRP) in this TLS.

svcTlsExtMmrpRegAttrCnt.name: svcTlsExtMmrpRegAttrCnt
svcTlsExtMmrpRegAttrCnt.description: The value of the object svcTlsExtMmrpRegAttrCnt indicates the number of MMRP attributes currently associated to the TLS by being registered.

svcTlsExtMmrpDeclaredAttrCnt.name: svcTlsExtMmrpDeclaredAttrCnt
svcTlsExtMmrpDeclaredAttrCnt.description: The value of the object svcTlsExtMmrpDeclaredAttrCnt indicates the number of MMRP attributes currently associated to the TLS by being declared.

svcTlsExtMmrpFailedRegCnt.name: svcTlsExtMmrpFailedRegCnt
svcTlsExtMmrpFailedRegCnt.description: The value of the object svcTlsExtMvrpFailedRegCnt indicates number of failed MMRP attribute registrations in this TLS.

svcTlsExtMvrpAttributeCount.name: svcTlsExtMvrpAttributeCount
svcTlsExtMvrpAttributeCount.description: The value of the object svcTlsExtMvrpAttributeCount indicates the number of MVRP attributes currently associated to the TLS by either being registered or declared.

svcTlsExtMmrpEndStationOnly.name: svcTlsExtMmrpEndStationOnly
svcTlsExtMmrpEndStationOnly.description: The value of the object svcTlsExtMmrpEndStationOnly specifies whether all SAP/SDP in this service are MMRP end-stations only.

svcTlsExtMacReNotifInterval.name: svcTlsExtMacReNotifInterval
svcTlsExtMacReNotifInterval.description: The value of svcTlsExtMacReNotifInterval specifies time-interval between subsequent burst of MAC notification messages. The default value indicates that the re-notification is disabled.

svcTlsExtSpbmCtrlVpls.name: svcTlsExtSpbmCtrlVpls
svcTlsExtSpbmCtrlVpls.description: The value of the object svcTlsExtSpbmCtrlVpls specifies the controlling Shortest Path Bridging (SPB) VPLS for this user SPB VPLS. An 'inconsistentValue' error is returned if svcTlsExtSpbmCtrlVpls is set to default and svcTlsExtSpbmFid is set to its non-default value or when svcTlsExtSpbmCtrlVpls is set to non-default and svcTlsExtSpbmFid is set to its default value.

svcTlsExtSpbmFid.name: svcTlsExtSpbmFid
svcTlsExtSpbmFid.description: The value of the object svcTlsExtSpbmFid specifies the forwarding database identifier used by the user SPB VPLS. An 'inconsistentValue' error is returned if svcTlsExtSpbmCtrlVpls is set to default and svcTlsExtSpbmFid is set to its non-default value or when svcTlsExtSpbmCtrlVpls is set to non-default and svcTlsExtSpbmFid is set to its default value.

svcPwRtLclPrefixTblLastChanged.name: svcPwRtLclPrefixTblLastChanged
svcPwRtLclPrefixTblLastChanged.description: The value of svcPwRtLclPrefixTblLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of svcPwRtLclPrefixTable. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcPwRtLclPrefixTable.name: svcPwRtLclPrefixTable
svcPwRtLclPrefixTable.description: A table that contains pseudo-wire routing local prefix information.

svcPwRtLclPrefixEntry.name: svcPwRtLclPrefixEntry
svcPwRtLclPrefixEntry.description: An entry indicating pseudo-wire routing local prefix information.

svcPwRtLclPrefixGlobalId.name: svcPwRtLclPrefixGlobalId
svcPwRtLclPrefixGlobalId.description: The value of the object svcPwRtLclPrefixGlobalId specifies the pseudo-wire routing global identifier.

svcPwRtLclPrefix.name: svcPwRtLclPrefix
svcPwRtLclPrefix.description: The value of the object svcPwRtLclPrefix specifies prefix value used by this pseudo-wire instance for redundancy.

svcPwRtLclPrefixRowStatus.name: svcPwRtLclPrefixRowStatus
svcPwRtLclPrefixRowStatus.description: This value of the object svcPwRtLclPrefixRowStatus specifies the status of this row.

svcPwRtLclPrefixLastChange.name: svcPwRtLclPrefixLastChange
svcPwRtLclPrefixLastChange.description: The value of svcPwRtLclPrefixLastChange indicates the timestamp of last change to this row in svcPwRtLclPrefixTable.

svcPwRtPathTblLastChanged.name: svcPwRtPathTblLastChanged
svcPwRtPathTblLastChanged.description: The value of svcPwRtPathTblLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of svcPwRtPathTable. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcPwRtPathTable.name: svcPwRtPathTable
svcPwRtPathTable.description: A table that contains pseudo-wire routing global path information.

svcPwRtPathEntry.name: svcPwRtPathEntry
svcPwRtPathEntry.description: An entry indicating global pseudo-wire routing path information.

svcPwRtPathName.name: svcPwRtPathName
svcPwRtPathName.description: The value of the object svcPwRtPathName specifies the path name in pseudo-wire routing global instance.

svcPwRtPathRowStatus.name: svcPwRtPathRowStatus
svcPwRtPathRowStatus.description: This value of the object svcPwRtPathRowStatus specifies the status of this row.

svcPwRtPathLastChange.name: svcPwRtPathLastChange
svcPwRtPathLastChange.description: The value of svcPwRtPathLastChange indicates the timestamp of last change to this row in svcPwRtPathTable.

svcPwRtPathAdminStatus.name: svcPwRtPathAdminStatus
svcPwRtPathAdminStatus.description: The value of svcPwRtPathAdminStatus specifies the administrative state of this path.

svcPwRtPathHopTblLastChgd.name: svcPwRtPathHopTblLastChgd
svcPwRtPathHopTblLastChgd.description: The value of svcPwRtPathHopTblLastChgd indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of svcPwRtPathHopTable. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcPwRtPathHopTable.name: svcPwRtPathHopTable
svcPwRtPathHopTable.description: A table that contains hop information per path in the pseudo-wire routing instances.

svcPwRtPathHopEntry.name: svcPwRtPathHopEntry
svcPwRtPathHopEntry.description: An entry indicating specific pseudo-wire routing path hop information.

svcPwRtPathHopIndex.name: svcPwRtPathHopIndex
svcPwRtPathHopIndex.description: The value of the object svcPwRtPathHopIndex specifies the hop index for the path in pseudo-wire routing global instance.

svcPwRtPathHopRowStatus.name: svcPwRtPathHopRowStatus
svcPwRtPathHopRowStatus.description: This value of the object svcPwRtPathHopRowStatus specifies the status of this row.

svcPwRtPathHopLastChange.name: svcPwRtPathHopLastChange
svcPwRtPathHopLastChange.description: The value of svcPwRtPathHopLastChange indicates the timestamp of last change to this row in svcPwRtPathHopTable.

svcPwRtPathHopAddrType.name: svcPwRtPathHopAddrType
svcPwRtPathHopAddrType.description: The value of svcPwRtPathHopAddrType specifies the address type of the address specified by svcPwRtPathHopAddr.

svcPwRtPathHopAddr.name: svcPwRtPathHopAddr
svcPwRtPathHopAddr.description: The value of svcPwRtPathHopAddr specifies the address associated with this hop.

svcPwRtStaticRtTblLastChgd.name: svcPwRtStaticRtTblLastChgd
svcPwRtStaticRtTblLastChgd.description: The value of svcPwRtStaticRtTblLastChgd indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of svcPwRtStaticRtTable. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcPwRtStaticRtTable.name: svcPwRtStaticRtTable
svcPwRtStaticRtTable.description: A table that contains static-route information for the pseudo-wire routing instances.

svcPwRtStaticRtEntry.name: svcPwRtStaticRtEntry
svcPwRtStaticRtEntry.description: An entry indicating specific static-route for the pseudo-wire routing instance.

svcPwRtStaticRtDstGlobalId.name: svcPwRtStaticRtDstGlobalId
svcPwRtStaticRtDstGlobalId.description: The value of the object svcPwRtStaticRtDstGlobalId specifies the pseudo-wire global routing index of the destination.

svcPwRtStaticRtDstPrefix.name: svcPwRtStaticRtDstPrefix
svcPwRtStaticRtDstPrefix.description: The value of the object svcPwRtStaticRtDstPrefix specifies the prefix of the global routing index of the destination.

svcPwRtStaticRtDstAddrType.name: svcPwRtStaticRtDstAddrType
svcPwRtStaticRtDstAddrType.description: The value of svcPwRtStaticRtDstAddrType specifies the address type of the address specified by svcPwRtStaticRtDstAddr.

svcPwRtStaticRtDstAddr.name: svcPwRtStaticRtDstAddr
svcPwRtStaticRtDstAddr.description: The value of svcPwRtStaticRtDstAddr specifies the destination address of this static-route entry.

svcPwRtStaticRtRowStatus.name: svcPwRtStaticRtRowStatus
svcPwRtStaticRtRowStatus.description: This value of the object svcPwRtStaticRtRowStatus specifies the status of this row.

svcPwRtStaticRtLastChange.name: svcPwRtStaticRtLastChange
svcPwRtStaticRtLastChange.description: The value of svcPwRtStaticRtLastChange indicates the timestamp of last change to this row in svcPwRtStaticRtTable.

svcMSPwPeTblLastChanged.name: svcMSPwPeTblLastChanged
svcMSPwPeTblLastChanged.description: The value of svcMSPwPeTblLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of svcMSPwPeTable. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcMSPwPeTable.name: svcMSPwPeTable
svcMSPwPeTable.description: A table that contains multi-segment pseudo-wire provider- edge information for the service.

svcMSPwPeEntry.name: svcMSPwPeEntry
svcMSPwPeEntry.description: Multi-segment pseudo-wire provider-edge specific information for this service.

svcMSPwPeId.name: svcMSPwPeId
svcMSPwPeId.description: The value of the object svcMSPwPeId specifies the multi-segment pseudo-wire provider-edge identifier for this service.

svcMSPwPeRowStatus.name: svcMSPwPeRowStatus
svcMSPwPeRowStatus.description: This value of the object svcMSPwPeRowStatus specifies the status of this row.

svcMSPwPeLastChange.name: svcMSPwPeLastChange
svcMSPwPeLastChange.description: The value of svcMSPwPeLastChange indicates the timestamp of last change to this row in svcMSPwPeTable.

svcMSPwPeAdminStatus.name: svcMSPwPeAdminStatus
svcMSPwPeAdminStatus.description: The value of svcMSPwPeAdminStatus specifies the administrative state of this multi-segment pseudo-wire provider-edge for this service.

svcMSPwPeFecType.name: svcMSPwPeFecType
svcMSPwPeFecType.description: The value of svcMSPwPeFecType specifies the LDP FEC type to be used on this multi-segment pseudo-wire provider-edge for this service.

svcMSPwPeAiiType.name: svcMSPwPeAiiType
svcMSPwPeAiiType.description: The value of svcMSPwPeAiiType specifies the Attachment Individual Identifier (AII) type to be used on this multi-segment pseudo-wire provider-edge for this service.

svcMSPwPeSignaling.name: svcMSPwPeSignaling
svcMSPwPeSignaling.description: The value of svcMSPwPeSignaling specifies the type of signaling used by this multi-segment pseudo-wire provider-edge for this service.

svcMSPwPeAutoConfig.name: svcMSPwPeAutoConfig
svcMSPwPeAutoConfig.description: The value of svcMSPwPeAutoConfig specifies whether multi-segment pseudo-wire provider-edge for this service should use auto-configuration.

svcMSPwPeAgi.name: svcMSPwPeAgi
svcMSPwPeAgi.description: The value of svcMSPwPeAgi specifies the Attachment Group Identifier (AGI) portion of the Generalized Id FEC element of the pseudo-wire setup for this provider-edge in this service.

svcMSPwPePolicyId.name: svcMSPwPePolicyId
svcMSPwPePolicyId.description: The value of svcMSPwPePolicyId specifies the pseudo-wite template policy to be used on this multi-segment pseudo-wire provider-edge.

svcMSPwPePrecedence.name: svcMSPwPePrecedence
svcMSPwPePrecedence.description: The value of svcMSPwPePrecedence specifies the precedence of this multi-segment pseudo-wire provider-edge in this service.

svcMSPwPeRetryTimer.name: svcMSPwPeRetryTimer
svcMSPwPeRetryTimer.description: The value of svcMSPwPeRetryTimer specifies the retry timer value to be used by this multi-segment pseudo-wire provider-edge in this service. System uses the value of svcPwRtRetryTimer when value of this object is set to the default.

svcMSPwPeRetryCount.name: svcMSPwPeRetryCount
svcMSPwPeRetryCount.description: The value of svcMSPwPeRetryCount specifies the retry count value to be used by this multi-segment pseudo-wire provider-edge in this service. System uses the value of svcPwRtRetryCount when value of this object is set to the default.

svcMSPwPeSaiiGlobalId.name: svcMSPwPeSaiiGlobalId
svcMSPwPeSaiiGlobalId.description: The value of svcMSPwPeSaiiGlobalId specifies the global identifier of Source Attachment Individual Identifier (SAII) portion of the Generalized Id FEC element as used by this multi-segment pseudo-wire provider-edge in this service.

svcMSPwPeSaiiPrefix.name: svcMSPwPeSaiiPrefix
svcMSPwPeSaiiPrefix.description: The value of svcMSPwPeSaiiPrefix specifies the prefix to the Source Attachment Individual Identifier (SAII) portion of the Generalized Id FEC element as used by this multi-segment pseudo-wire provider-edge in this service.

svcMSPwPeSaiiAcId.name: svcMSPwPeSaiiAcId
svcMSPwPeSaiiAcId.description: The value of svcMSPwPeSaiiAcId specifies the attachment circuit identifier part of Source Attachment Individual Identifier (SAII) portion of the Generalized Id FEC element as used by this multi-segment pseudo-wire provider-edge in this service.

svcMSPwPeTaiiGlobalId.name: svcMSPwPeTaiiGlobalId
svcMSPwPeTaiiGlobalId.description: The value of svcMSPwPeTaiiGlobalId specifies the global identifier of Target Attachment Individual Identifier (TAII) portion of the Generalized Id FEC element as used by this multi-segment pseudo-wire provider-edge in this service.

svcMSPwPeTaiiPrefix.name: svcMSPwPeTaiiPrefix
svcMSPwPeTaiiPrefix.description: The value of svcMSPwPeTaiiPrefix specifies the prefix to the Target Attachment Individual Identifier (TAII) portion of the Generalized Id FEC element as used by this multi-segment pseudo-wire provider-edge in this service.

svcMSPwPeTaiiAcId.name: svcMSPwPeTaiiAcId
svcMSPwPeTaiiAcId.description: The value of svcMSPwPeTaiiAcId specifies the attachment circuit identifier part of Target Attachment Individual Identifier (TAII) portion of the Generalized Id FEC element as used by this multi-segment pseudo-wire provider-edge in this service.

svcMSPwPePathName.name: svcMSPwPePathName
svcMSPwPePathName.description: The value of svcMSPwPePathName specifies the path name used by this multi-segment pseudo-wire provider-edge in this service.

svcMSPwPeEndPoint.name: svcMSPwPeEndPoint
svcMSPwPeEndPoint.description: The value of svcMSPwPeEndPoint specifies the endpoint used by this multi-segment pseudo-wire provider-edge in this service.

svcMSPwPeStandbySigSlave.name: svcMSPwPeStandbySigSlave
svcMSPwPeStandbySigSlave.description: The value of svcMSPwPeStandbySigSlave specifies whether transmission of any spoke in the endpoint will be blocked when the spoke receives standby status notification from its peer.

svcMSPwPeIsICB.name: svcMSPwPeIsICB
svcMSPwPeIsICB.description: The value of svcMSPwPeIsICB specifies whether this sdp-binding is an inter-chassis backup SDP bind.

svcMSPwPeTimeRemain.name: svcMSPwPeTimeRemain
svcMSPwPeTimeRemain.description: The value of svcMSPwPeTimeRemain indicates remaining time in the retry timer for this multi-segment pseudo-wire provider-edge in this service.

svcMSPwPeRetryRemain.name: svcMSPwPeRetryRemain
svcMSPwPeRetryRemain.description: The value of svcMSPwPeRetryRemain indicates remaining retries for this multi-segment pseudo-wire provider-edge in this service.

svcMSPwPeOperSdpBind.name: svcMSPwPeOperSdpBind
svcMSPwPeOperSdpBind.description: The value of svcMSPwPeOperSdpBind indicates operational SDP-bind used for this multi-segment pseudo-wire provider-edge in this service.

svcMSPwPeRetryExpired.name: svcMSPwPeRetryExpired
svcMSPwPeRetryExpired.description: The value of svcMSPwPeRetryExpired indicates whether all retries have expired for this multi-segment pseudo-wire provider-edge in this service.

svcMSPwPeLastError.name: svcMSPwPeLastError
svcMSPwPeLastError.description: The value of the object svcMSPwPeLastError indicates the last error encountered trying to bring up this multi-segment pseudo-wire provider-edge in this service.

svcOperGrpTblLastChanged.name: svcOperGrpTblLastChanged
svcOperGrpTblLastChanged.description: The value of svcOperGrpTblLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of svcOperGrpTable. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcOperGrpTable.name: svcOperGrpTable
svcOperGrpTable.description: A table that contains Operational-Group information.

svcOperGrpEntry.name: svcOperGrpEntry
svcOperGrpEntry.description: Each row specifies information about a specific Operational-Group.

svcOperGrpName.name: svcOperGrpName
svcOperGrpName.description: The value of the object svcOperGrpName specifies the Operational-Group identifier.

svcOperGrpRowStatus.name: svcOperGrpRowStatus
svcOperGrpRowStatus.description: This value of the object svcOperGrpRowStatus specifies the status of this row.

svcOperGrpLastChange.name: svcOperGrpLastChange
svcOperGrpLastChange.description: The value of svcOperGrpLastChange indicates the timestamp of last change to this row in svcOperGrpTable.

svcOperGrpOperStatus.name: svcOperGrpOperStatus
svcOperGrpOperStatus.description: The value of svcOperGrpOperStatus indicates the operational state of this group.

svcOperGrpHoldDownTime.name: svcOperGrpHoldDownTime
svcOperGrpHoldDownTime.description: The value of svcOperGrpHoldDownTime specifies number of seconds to wait before notifying clients monitoring this group when its operational status transitions from up to down.

svcOperGrpCreationOrigin.name: svcOperGrpCreationOrigin
svcOperGrpCreationOrigin.description: The value of svcOperGrpCreationOrigin indicates the protocol or mechanism which created this group.

svcOperGrpHoldUpTime.name: svcOperGrpHoldUpTime
svcOperGrpHoldUpTime.description: The value of svcOperGrpHoldUpTime specifies number of seconds to wait before notifying clients monitoring this group when its operational status transitions from down to up.

svcOperGrpHoldUpTimeRemain.name: svcOperGrpHoldUpTimeRemain
svcOperGrpHoldUpTimeRemain.description: The value of svcOperGrpHoldUpTimeRemain indicates the number of seconds remaining in the svcOperGrpHoldUpTime.

svcOperGrpHoldDownTimeRemain.name: svcOperGrpHoldDownTimeRemain
svcOperGrpHoldDownTimeRemain.description: The value of svcOperGrpHoldDownTimeRemain indicates the number of seconds remaining in the svcOperGrpHoldDownTime.

svcOperGrpNumMembers.name: svcOperGrpNumMembers
svcOperGrpNumMembers.description: The value of svcOperGrpNumMembers indicates the number of members as part of this operational-group.

svcOperGrpNumMonitoring.name: svcOperGrpNumMonitoring
svcOperGrpNumMonitoring.description: The value of svcOperGrpNumMonitoring indicates the number of objects monitoring this operational-group.

svcDhcpLeaseAleTable.name: svcDhcpLeaseAleTable
svcDhcpLeaseAleTable.description: The svcDhcpLeaseAleTable contains Access Loop Encapsulation information for DHCP lease states. Entries in this table are created and destroyed by the system. This table is a sparse augment of the svcDhcpLeaseTable: entries are created only for DHCP lease states for which Access Loop Encapsulation information is available.

svcDhcpLeaseAleEntry.name: svcDhcpLeaseAleEntry
svcDhcpLeaseAleEntry.description: Each conceptual row represents access loop encapsulation information of a DHCP lease state.

svcDhcpLeaseAleDatalink.name: svcDhcpLeaseAleDatalink
svcDhcpLeaseAleDatalink.description: The value of svcDhcpLeaseAleDatalink indicates the data link used by the subscriber host on the DSL access loop.

svcDhcpLeaseAleEncaps1.name: svcDhcpLeaseAleEncaps1
svcDhcpLeaseAleEncaps1.description: The value of svcDhcpLeaseAleEncaps1 indicates the encapsulation used by the subscriber host on the DSL access loop.

svcDhcpLeaseAleEncaps2.name: svcDhcpLeaseAleEncaps2
svcDhcpLeaseAleEncaps2.description: The value of svcDhcpLeaseAleEncaps2 indicates the encapsulation used by the subscriber host on the DSL access loop.

svcEthCfmTblLastChanged.name: svcEthCfmTblLastChanged
svcEthCfmTblLastChanged.description: The value of svcEthCfmTblLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of svcEthCfmTable. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcEthCfmTable.name: svcEthCfmTable
svcEthCfmTable.description: The svcEthCfmTable contains Ethernet Connectivity Fault Management (CFM) information for Ethernet capable Services.

svcEthCfmEntry.name: svcEthCfmEntry
svcEthCfmEntry.description: The svcEthCfmEntry consists of the Eth-CFM objects used to maintain Ethernet CFM functionality for the specified Ethernet capable Service.

svcEthCfmTunnelFaultNotification.name: svcEthCfmTunnelFaultNotification
svcEthCfmTunnelFaultNotification.description: The value of svcEthCfmTunnelFaultNotification specifies whether the service will 'accept (1)' CFM fault notification from a Tunnel MEP and process the notification (i.e. do fault handling and/or fault propagation), or 'ignore (2)' the notification. Both TIMETRA-SAP-MIB::sapEthCfmTunnelFaultNotification and this object MUST be set to 'accept (1)' for an individual SAP to process the notification.

svcEthCfmVMepExtensions.name: svcEthCfmVMepExtensions
svcEthCfmVMepExtensions.description: The value of svcEthCfmVMepExtensions specifies whether enhanced Virtual MEP functionality is enabled on the service or not. This object is used by TLS (VPLS) services only, and has no effect nor can it be modified on other service types. On services that do not support VMEP extensions this object is fixed to the value 'disabled (2)'.

svcMacFdbRecords.name: svcMacFdbRecords
svcMacFdbRecords.description: The value of the object svcMacFdbRecords indicates the number of system wide FDB records in use.

svcPwRtSpeAddrGlobalId.name: svcPwRtSpeAddrGlobalId
svcPwRtSpeAddrGlobalId.description: The value of the object svcPwRtSpeAddrGlobalId specifies the pseudo- wire routing global identifier of the switch-point node. An 'inconsistentValue' error is returned if svcPwRtSpeAddrGlobalId is set to default when svcPwRtSpeAddrPrefix is set to non-default value or svcPwRtSpeAddrGlobalId is set to non-default when svcPwRtSpeAddrPrefix is set to default value.

svcPwRtSpeAddrPrefix.name: svcPwRtSpeAddrPrefix
svcPwRtSpeAddrPrefix.description: The value of the object svcPwRtSpeAddrPrefix specifies the pseudo-wire routing prefix of the switch-point node. An 'inconsistentValue' error is returned if svcPwRtSpeAddrGlobalId is set to default when svcPwRtSpeAddrPrefix is set to non-default value or svcPwRtSpeAddrGlobalId is set to non-default when svcPwRtSpeAddrPrefix is set to default value.

svcPwRtBootTimer.name: svcPwRtBootTimer
svcPwRtBootTimer.description: The value of the object svcPwRtBootTimer specifies how long the system waits after the reboot before trying to establish multi-segment pseudo-wire provider-edge connections.

svcPwRtRetryTimer.name: svcPwRtRetryTimer
svcPwRtRetryTimer.description: The value of svcPwRtRetryTimer specifies the retry timer value to be used by this multi-segment pseudo-wire provider-edge in this service.

svcPwRtRetryCount.name: svcPwRtRetryCount
svcPwRtRetryCount.description: The value of svcPwRtRetryCount specifies the retry count value to be used by this multi-segment pseudo-wire provider-edge in this service.

svcPwRtBgpRoutes.name: svcPwRtBgpRoutes
svcPwRtBgpRoutes.description: The value of svcPwRtBgpRoutes indicates the number of BGP routes in the TIMETRA-VRTR-MIB::vRtrMsPwL2RtTable.

svcPwRtStaticRoutes.name: svcPwRtStaticRoutes
svcPwRtStaticRoutes.description: The value of svcPwRtStaticRoutes indicates the number of static routes in the TIMETRA-VRTR-MIB::vRtrMsPwL2RtTable.

svcPwRtLocalRoutes.name: svcPwRtLocalRoutes
svcPwRtLocalRoutes.description: The value of svcPwRtLocalRoutes indicates the number of local routes in the TIMETRA-VRTR-MIB::vRtrMsPwL2RtTable.

svcPwRtHostRoutes.name: svcPwRtHostRoutes
svcPwRtHostRoutes.description: The value of svcPwRtHostRoutes indicates the number of host routes in the TIMETRA-VRTR-MIB::vRtrMsPwL2RtTable.

svcPwRtBootTimerRemain.name: svcPwRtBootTimerRemain
svcPwRtBootTimerRemain.description: The value of svcPwRtBootTimerRemain indicates the number of seconds remaining in the svcPwRtBootTimer.

svcPwRtLclPfxRDTblLastChanged.name: svcPwRtLclPfxRDTblLastChanged
svcPwRtLclPfxRDTblLastChanged.description: The value of svcPwRtLclPfxRDTblLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of svcPwRtLclPfxRDTable. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcPwRtLclPfxRDTable.name: svcPwRtLclPfxRDTable
svcPwRtLclPfxRDTable.description: A table that contains pseudo-wire routing local prefix route- distingiusher information.

svcPwRtLclPfxRDEntry.name: svcPwRtLclPfxRDEntry
svcPwRtLclPfxRDEntry.description: An entry indicating pseudo-wire routing local prefix route- distinguisher information.

svcPwRtLclPfxRD.name: svcPwRtLclPfxRD
svcPwRtLclPfxRD.description: The value of svcPwRtLclPfxRD specifies the route-disinguisher assoicated with this prefix.

svcPwRtLclPfxRDRowStatus.name: svcPwRtLclPfxRDRowStatus
svcPwRtLclPfxRDRowStatus.description: This value of the object svcPwRtLclPfxRDRowStatus specifies the status of this row.

svcPwRtLclPfxRDLastChange.name: svcPwRtLclPfxRDLastChange
svcPwRtLclPfxRDLastChange.description: The value of svcPwRtLclPfxRDLastChange indicates the timestamp of last change to this row in svcPwRtLclPfxRDTable.

svcPwRtLclPfxRDCommunity.name: svcPwRtLclPfxRDCommunity
svcPwRtLclPfxRDCommunity.description: The value of the object svcPwRtLclPfxRDCommunity specifies the BGP community associated with the route-distinguisher.

svcPwSpeSaiiTable.name: svcPwSpeSaiiTable
svcPwSpeSaiiTable.description: A table that contains pseudo-wire switch-point node information by Source Attachment Individual Identifier (SAII).

svcPwSpeSaiiEntry.name: svcPwSpeSaiiEntry
svcPwSpeSaiiEntry.description: An entry that contains pseudo-wire switch-point node information by Source Attachment Individual Identifier (SAII).

svcPwSpeSaiiTaiiGlobalId.name: svcPwSpeSaiiTaiiGlobalId
svcPwSpeSaiiTaiiGlobalId.description: The value of svcPwSpeSaiiTaiiGlobalId indicates the global identifier of Target Attachment Individual Identifier (TAII) portion of the Generalized Id FEC element on switch-point node.

svcPwSpeSaiiTaiiPrefix.name: svcPwSpeSaiiTaiiPrefix
svcPwSpeSaiiTaiiPrefix.description: The value of svcPwSpeSaiiTaiiPrefix indicates the prefix to the Target Attachment Individual Identifier (TAII) portion of the Generalized Id FEC element on switch-point node.

svcPwSpeSaiiTaiiAcId.name: svcPwSpeSaiiTaiiAcId
svcPwSpeSaiiTaiiAcId.description: The value of svcPwSpeSaiiTaiiAcId indicates the attachment circuit identifier part of Source Attachment Individual Identifier (SAII) portion of the Generalized Id FEC element on switch-point node.

svcPwSpeSaiiSvcId.name: svcPwSpeSaiiSvcId
svcPwSpeSaiiSvcId.description: The value of svcPwSpeSaiiSvcId indicates the Service identifier on this switch-point node.

svcPwSpeSaiiOperSdpBind1.name: svcPwSpeSaiiOperSdpBind1
svcPwSpeSaiiOperSdpBind1.description: The value of svcPwSpeSaiiOperSdpBind1 indicates the first operational SDP-bind on this switch-point node.

svcPwSpeSaiiOperSdpBind2.name: svcPwSpeSaiiOperSdpBind2
svcPwSpeSaiiOperSdpBind2.description: The value of svcPwSpeSaiiOperSdpBind2 indicates the other operational SDP-bind on this switch-point node.

svcPwSpeTaiiTable.name: svcPwSpeTaiiTable
svcPwSpeTaiiTable.description: A table that contains pseudo-wire switch-point node information by Target Attachment Individual Identifier (TAII).

svcPwSpeTaiiEntry.name: svcPwSpeTaiiEntry
svcPwSpeTaiiEntry.description: An entry that contains pseudo-wire switch-point node information by Target Attachment Individual Identifier (TAII).

svcPwSpeTaiiSaiiGlobalId.name: svcPwSpeTaiiSaiiGlobalId
svcPwSpeTaiiSaiiGlobalId.description: The value of svcPwSpeTaiiSaiiGlobalId indicates the global identifier of Source Attachment Individual Identifier (SAII) portion of the Generalized Id FEC element on switch-point node.

svcPwSpeTaiiSaiiPrefix.name: svcPwSpeTaiiSaiiPrefix
svcPwSpeTaiiSaiiPrefix.description: The value of svcPwSpeTaiiSaiiPrefix indicates the prefix to the Source Attachment Individual Identifier (SAII) portion of the Generalized Id FEC element on switch-point node.

svcPwSpeTaiiSaiiAcId.name: svcPwSpeTaiiSaiiAcId
svcPwSpeTaiiSaiiAcId.description: The value of svcPwSpeTaiiSaiiAcId indicates the attachment circuit identifier part of Target Attachment Individual Identifier (TAII) portion of the Generalized Id FEC element on switch-point node.

svcPwSpeTaiiSvcId.name: svcPwSpeTaiiSvcId
svcPwSpeTaiiSvcId.description: The value of svcPwSpeTaiiSvcId indicates the Service identifier on this switch-point node.

svcPwSpeTaiiOperSdpBind1.name: svcPwSpeTaiiOperSdpBind1
svcPwSpeTaiiOperSdpBind1.description: The value of svcPwSpeTaiiOperSdpBind1 indicates the first operational SDP-bind on this switch-point node.

svcPwSpeTaiiOperSdpBind2.name: svcPwSpeTaiiOperSdpBind2
svcPwSpeTaiiOperSdpBind2.description: The value of svcPwSpeTaiiOperSdpBind2 indicates the other operational SDP-bind on this switch-point node.

svcDhcpLeaseOvrTable.name: svcDhcpLeaseOvrTable
svcDhcpLeaseOvrTable.description: The svcDhcpLeaseOvrTable contains QoS (Quality of Service) overrides for DHCP lease states. Entries in this table are created and destroyed by the system. This table is a sparse augment of the svcDhcpLeaseTable: entries are created only for DHCP lease states for which QoS overrides information is available.

svcDhcpLeaseOvrEntry.name: svcDhcpLeaseOvrEntry
svcDhcpLeaseOvrEntry.description: Each conceptual row represents QoS overrides information of a DHCP lease state.

svcDhcpLeaseOvrDirection.name: svcDhcpLeaseOvrDirection
svcDhcpLeaseOvrDirection.description: The value of svcDhcpLeaseOvrDirection indicates if this row specifies ingress or egress qos override parameters.

svcDhcpLeaseOvrType.name: svcDhcpLeaseOvrType
svcDhcpLeaseOvrType.description: The value of svcDhcpLeaseOvrType indicates what field has been overridden by this row.

svcDhcpLeaseOvrTypeId.name: svcDhcpLeaseOvrTypeId
svcDhcpLeaseOvrTypeId.description: The value of svcDhcpLeaseOvrTypeId indicates the ID of the queue/policer that has been overridden by this row. If the value of svcDhcpLeaseOvrType is not 'queue (1)' or 'policer (2)', this field must be set to zero (0).

svcDhcpLeaseOvrTypeName.name: svcDhcpLeaseOvrTypeName
svcDhcpLeaseOvrTypeName.description: The value of svcDhcpLeaseOvrTypeName indicates the name of the scheduler/arbiter that has been overridden by this row. If the value of svcDhcpLeaseOvrType is not 'arbiter (4)' or 'scheduler (5)', this field must be set to zero (0).

svcDhcpLeaseOvrPIR.name: svcDhcpLeaseOvrPIR
svcDhcpLeaseOvrPIR.description: The value of svcDhcpLeaseOvrPIR indicates the PIR rate in kbps allowed for the object overridden by this row.

svcDhcpLeaseOvrCIR.name: svcDhcpLeaseOvrCIR
svcDhcpLeaseOvrCIR.description: The value of svcDhcpLeaseOvrCIR indicates the CIR rate in kbps allowed for the object overridden by this row.

svcDhcpLeaseOvrCBS.name: svcDhcpLeaseOvrCBS
svcDhcpLeaseOvrCBS.description: The value of svcDhcpLeaseOvrCBS indicates the amount of reserved buffer space (in bytes) for the object overridden by this row.

svcDhcpLeaseOvrMBS.name: svcDhcpLeaseOvrMBS
svcDhcpLeaseOvrMBS.description: The value of svcDhcpLeaseOvrMBS indicates the maximum amount of reserved buffer space (in bytes) for the object overridden by this row.

svcDhcpLeaseOvrWrrWeight.name: svcDhcpLeaseOvrWrrWeight
svcDhcpLeaseOvrWrrWeight.description: The value of svcDhcpLeaseOvrWrrWeight specifies the weight of this queue for the HSMDA scheduler. The weight determines how much bandwidth this queue gets out of the total rate for the scheduling class. The value of svcDhcpLeaseOvrWrrWeight is only relevant if the value of svcDhcpLeaseOvrType is equal to 'queue', and if the queue specified in svcDhcpLeaseOvrTypeId is referenced in the value of TIMETRA-QOS-MIB::tHsmdaWrrPolicyIncludeQueues of the Weighted Round Robin policy associated wit this PPP session.

svcTlsSpbTableLastChanged.name: svcTlsSpbTableLastChanged
svcTlsSpbTableLastChanged.description: The value of svcTlsSpbTableLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of svcTlsSpbTable. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcTlsSpbTable.name: svcTlsSpbTable
svcTlsSpbTable.description: svcTlsSpbTable contains entries for Shortest Path Bridging in a VPLS service context.

svcTlsSpbEntry.name: svcTlsSpbEntry
svcTlsSpbEntry.description: A Shortest Path Bridging entry in the svcTlsSpbTable.

svcTlsSpbRowStatus.name: svcTlsSpbRowStatus
svcTlsSpbRowStatus.description: The value of svcTlsSpbRowStatus is used for the creation and deletion of Shortest Path Bridging context in a VPLS service.

svcTlsSpbLastChanged.name: svcTlsSpbLastChanged
svcTlsSpbLastChanged.description: The value of svcTlsSpbLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of this entry. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcTlsSpbIsisInstance.name: svcTlsSpbIsisInstance
svcTlsSpbIsisInstance.description: The value of svcTlsSpbIsisInstance specifies the ISIS-MIB::isisSysInstance to be used with this Shortest Path Bridging context in this VPLS service. An 'inconsistentValue' error is returned if value of svcTlsSpbIsisInstance is set to a different value after the row-creation time.

svcTlsSpbFid.name: svcTlsSpbFid
svcTlsSpbFid.description: The value of svcTlsSpbFid specifies forwarding database identifier associated with this Shortest Path Bridging context in this VPLS service. An 'inconsistentValue' error is returned if value of svcTlsSpbFid is set to a different value after the row-creation time.

svcTlsSpbL1BridgePriority.name: svcTlsSpbL1BridgePriority
svcTlsSpbL1BridgePriority.description: The value of svcTlsSpbL1BridgePriority specifies the level 1 four bit bridge priority associated with this Shortest Path Bridging context in this VPLS service.

svcTlsSpbL1FwdTreeTopoUcast.name: svcTlsSpbL1FwdTreeTopoUcast
svcTlsSpbL1FwdTreeTopoUcast.description: The value of svcTlsSpbL1FwdTreeTopoUcast specifies level 1 unicast forwarding to follow the shortest path tree or to follow a single tree for this Shortest Path Bridging context in this VPLS service.

svcTlsSpbAdminState.name: svcTlsSpbAdminState
svcTlsSpbAdminState.description: The svcTlsSpbAdminState indicates the desired administrative state for Shortest Path Bridging on this VPLS service.

svcTlsSpbL1FwdTreeTopoMcast.name: svcTlsSpbL1FwdTreeTopoMcast
svcTlsSpbL1FwdTreeTopoMcast.description: The value of svcTlsSpbL1FwdTreeTopoMcast indicates level 1 multicast forwarding to follow the shortest path tree or to follow a single tree for this Shortest Path Bridging context in this VPLS service.

svcTlsSpbL1BridgeId.name: svcTlsSpbL1BridgeId
svcTlsSpbL1BridgeId.description: The svcTlsSpbL1BridgeId indicates the level 1 designated bridge identifier for Shortest Path Bridging context on this VPLS service.

svcTlsSpbL1McastDesigBridgeId.name: svcTlsSpbL1McastDesigBridgeId
svcTlsSpbL1McastDesigBridgeId.description: The svcTlsSpbL1McastDesigBridgeId indicates the level 1 designated bridge identifier for multicast traffic for Shortest Path Bridging on this VPLS service.

svcVllBgpTableLastChanged.name: svcVllBgpTableLastChanged
svcVllBgpTableLastChanged.description: The value of svcVllBgpTableLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of svcVllBgpTable. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcVllBgpTable.name: svcVllBgpTable
svcVllBgpTable.description: The svcVllBgpTable contains entries for BGP in a VLL service context.

svcVllBgpEntry.name: svcVllBgpEntry
svcVllBgpEntry.description: The svcVllBgpEntry contains BGP related information for a specific service.

svcVllBgpRowStatus.name: svcVllBgpRowStatus
svcVllBgpRowStatus.description: The value of svcVllBgpRowStatus is used for the creation and deletion of Shortest Path Bridging context in a VPLS service.

svcVllBgpLastChanged.name: svcVllBgpLastChanged
svcVllBgpLastChanged.description: The value of svcVllBgpLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of this entry. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcVllBgpVsiRD.name: svcVllBgpVsiRD
svcVllBgpVsiRD.description: The value of svcVllBgpVsiRD specifies the high-order 6 bytes used to compose the Virtual Switch Instance identifier (VSI-id) to use for NLRI in BGP in this VLL service.

svcVllBgpExportRteTarget.name: svcVllBgpExportRteTarget
svcVllBgpExportRteTarget.description: The value of svcVllBgpExportRteTarget specifies the extended community name for the default export policy to use for BGP in this VLL service. This object cannot be set to a non-empty if svcVllBgpExportRteTarget has a non-empty value, otherwise an 'inconsistentValue' error will be returned.

svcVllBgpImportRteTarget.name: svcVllBgpImportRteTarget
svcVllBgpImportRteTarget.description: The value of svcVllBgpImportRteTarget specifies the extended community name for the default import policy to use for BGP in this VLL service. This object cannot be set to a non-empty if svcVllBgpImportRteTarget has a non-empty value, otherwise an 'inconsistentValue' error will be returned.

svcVllSiteIdTblLastChanged.name: svcVllSiteIdTblLastChanged
svcVllSiteIdTblLastChanged.description: The value of svcVllSiteIdTblLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of svcVllSiteIdTable. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcVllSiteIdTable.name: svcVllSiteIdTable
svcVllSiteIdTable.description: This table maintains the information about different sites defined in a service.

svcVllSiteIdEntry.name: svcVllSiteIdEntry
svcVllSiteIdEntry.description: The svcVllSiteIdEntry contains information about a particular site in a specific service.

svcVllSiteIdName.name: svcVllSiteIdName
svcVllSiteIdName.description: The value of svcVllSiteIdName defines the name for the specific site.

svcVllSiteIdRowStatus.name: svcVllSiteIdRowStatus
svcVllSiteIdRowStatus.description: The value of svcVllSiteIdRowStatus is used for the creation and deletion of rows in this table.

svcVllSiteIdLastChanged.name: svcVllSiteIdLastChanged
svcVllSiteIdLastChanged.description: The value of svcVllSiteIdLastChanged indicates the timestamp of last change to this row in svcVllSiteIdTable.

svcVllSiteIdAdminStatus.name: svcVllSiteIdAdminStatus
svcVllSiteIdAdminStatus.description: The value of svcVllSiteIdAdminStatus specifies the administrative state of the site instance associated with this service.

svcVllSiteIdSiteId.name: svcVllSiteIdSiteId
svcVllSiteIdSiteId.description: The value of svcVllSiteIdSiteId specifies the identifier for the site in this service.

svcVllSiteIdPortId.name: svcVllSiteIdPortId
svcVllSiteIdPortId.description: The value of svcVllSiteIdPortId specifies the port associated with this site. The default value for this object indicates an invalid port. An 'inconsistentValue' error is returned when svcVllSiteIdPortId is set to non-default and svcVllSiteIdEncapValue is set to its default value or when svcVllSiteIdPortId is set to its default value and svcVllSiteIdEncapValue is set to non-default value.

svcVllSiteIdEncapValue.name: svcVllSiteIdEncapValue
svcVllSiteIdEncapValue.description: The value of svcVllSiteIdEncapValue specifies the encap-value of the port associated with this site. An 'inconsistentValue' error is returned when svcVllSiteIdPortId is set to non-default and svcVllSiteIdEncapValue is set to its default value or when svcVllSiteIdPortId is set to its default value and svcVllSiteIdEncapValue is set to non-default value.

svcVllSiteIdOperStatus.name: svcVllSiteIdOperStatus
svcVllSiteIdOperStatus.description: The value of the svcVllSiteIdOperStatus indicates the operational status of the site.

svcVllSiteIdDesignatedFwdr.name: svcVllSiteIdDesignatedFwdr
svcVllSiteIdDesignatedFwdr.description: The value of the svcVllSiteIdDesignatedFwdr indicates whether this site has been declared as 'designated-forwarder' depending on the result of the BGP election.

svcVllSiteIdBootTimer.name: svcVllSiteIdBootTimer
svcVllSiteIdBootTimer.description: The value of svcVllSiteIdBootTimer specifies how long the system waits after a node reboot before running the DF (designated- forwarder) election algorithm. When this object is set to default value, system uses value of TIMETRA-MC-REDUNDANCY-MIB::tmnxMcRedBgpMultiHomeBootTimer object.

svcVllSiteIdSiteActTimer.name: svcVllSiteIdSiteActTimer
svcVllSiteIdSiteActTimer.description: The value of svcVllSiteIdSiteActTimer specifies the time-period the system keeps the local sites in standby status, waiting for BGP updates from remote PEs before running the DF (designated-forwarder) election algorithm to decide whether the site should be unblocked. When this object is set to default value, system uses value of TIMETRA-MC-REDUNDANCY-MIB::tmnxMcRedBgpMultiHomeSiteTimer object.

svcVllSiteIdDfUpTime.name: svcVllSiteIdDfUpTime
svcVllSiteIdDfUpTime.description: The value of svcVllSiteIdDfUpTime indicates the uptime of the designated forwarder for this site.

svcVllSiteIdDfChgCnt.name: svcVllSiteIdDfChgCnt
svcVllSiteIdDfChgCnt.description: The value of svcVllSiteIdDfChgCnt indicates the number of times designated forwarder has changed.

svcVllSiteIdTimerRemain.name: svcVllSiteIdTimerRemain
svcVllSiteIdTimerRemain.description: The value of svcVllSiteIdTimerRemain indicates remaining time in the timer for this site.

svcTlsPmsiTableLastChanged.name: svcTlsPmsiTableLastChanged
svcTlsPmsiTableLastChanged.description: The value of svcTlsPmsiTableLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of svcTlsPmsiTable. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcTlsPmsiTable.name: svcTlsPmsiTable
svcTlsPmsiTable.description: The svcTlsPmsiTable contains entries for provider-tunnel in a VPLS service context.

svcTlsPmsiEntry.name: svcTlsPmsiEntry
svcTlsPmsiEntry.description: The svcTlsPmsiEntry contains provider-tunnel related objects.

svcTlsPmsiRowStatus.name: svcTlsPmsiRowStatus
svcTlsPmsiRowStatus.description: The value of svcTlsPmsiRowStatus is used for the creation and deletion of provider-tunnel context in a VPLS service.

svcTlsPmsiLastChanged.name: svcTlsPmsiLastChanged
svcTlsPmsiLastChanged.description: The value of svcTlsPmsiLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of this entry. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcTlsIPmsiAdminState.name: svcTlsIPmsiAdminState
svcTlsIPmsiAdminState.description: The value of the object svcTlsIPmsiAdminState specifies the administrative state of the inclusive provider tunnel in this service. An 'inconsistentValue' error is retuned when attempting to set svcTlsIPmsiAdminState to 'inService' when svcTlsIPmsiType is set to 'none' or svcTlsIPmsiLspTmpl is set to its default value.

svcTlsIPmsiDataDelayIntvl.name: svcTlsIPmsiDataDelayIntvl
svcTlsIPmsiDataDelayIntvl.description: The value of the object svcTlsIPmsiDataDelayIntvl specifies the data delay interval associated for the inclusive provider tunnel in this service.

svcTlsIPmsiType.name: svcTlsIPmsiType
svcTlsIPmsiType.description: The value of the object svcTlsIPmsiType specifies the type of protocol supported for the inclusive provider tunnel in this service.

svcTlsIPmsiLspTmpl.name: svcTlsIPmsiLspTmpl
svcTlsIPmsiLspTmpl.description: The value of the object svcTlsIPmsiLspTmpl specifies the name of the TIMETRA-MPLS-MIB::vRtrMplsLspTemplateName to be used for signalling inclusive provider tunnel in this service. An 'inconsistentValue' error is returned if svcTlsIPmsiLspTmpl does not exist in TIMETRA-MPLS-MIB::vRtrMplsLspTemplateTable. An 'inconsistentValue' error is returned if this object is set to non-default when svcTlsIPmsiType is set to 'none'.

svcTlsIPmsiRootAndLeaf.name: svcTlsIPmsiRootAndLeaf
svcTlsIPmsiRootAndLeaf.description: The value of the object svcTlsIPmsiRootAndLeaf specifies whether the node acts as both a root and leaf or only act as a leaf for P2MP LSP.

svcTlsIPmsiRemainDataDelayIntvl.name: svcTlsIPmsiRemainDataDelayIntvl
svcTlsIPmsiRemainDataDelayIntvl.description: The value of the object svcTlsIPmsiRemainDataDelayIntvl indicates the remaining data delay interval for the inclusive provider tunnel in this service.

svcTlsIPmsiLspName.name: svcTlsIPmsiLspName
svcTlsIPmsiLspName.description: The value of the object svcTlsIPmsiLspTmpl indicates the LSP name used for signalling inclusive provider tunnel in this service.

svcDhcpLeaseWppTable.name: svcDhcpLeaseWppTable
svcDhcpLeaseWppTable.description: The svcDhcpLeaseWppTable is a sparse augment of the svcDhcpLeaseTable. It contains Web Portal Protocol (WPP) information associated with DHCP lease states.

svcDhcpLeaseWppEntry.name: svcDhcpLeaseWppEntry
svcDhcpLeaseWppEntry.description: Each row entry contains WPP information associated with a particular DHCP lease state.

svcDhcpLeaseWppState.name: svcDhcpLeaseWppState
svcDhcpLeaseWppState.description: The value of svcDhcpLeaseWppState indicates the WPP state for this lease state.

svcDhcpLeaseWppPortalRouter.name: svcDhcpLeaseWppPortalRouter
svcDhcpLeaseWppPortalRouter.description: The value of svcDhcpLeaseWppPortalRouter indicates the routing instance identifier of the WPP portal used for this lease state. The value zero indicates that the WPP portal is currently unknown.

svcDhcpLeaseWppPortalName.name: svcDhcpLeaseWppPortalName
svcDhcpLeaseWppPortalName.description: The value of svcDhcpLeaseWppPortalName indicates the name of the WPP portal used for this lease state. The value zero indicates that the WPP portal is currently unknown. The values of svcDhcpLeaseWppPortalRouter and svcDhcpLeaseWppPortalName refer to a conceptual row in the TIMETRA-WEB-PORTAL-MIB::tmnxWppPortalTable.

svcIfSapCfgTableLastChanged.name: svcIfSapCfgTableLastChanged
svcIfSapCfgTableLastChanged.description: The value of svcIfSapCfgTableLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of svcIfSapCfgTable. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

svcIfSapCfgTable.name: svcIfSapCfgTable
svcIfSapCfgTable.description: The svcIfSapCfgTable contains objects to configure (internal) SAP parameters for applicable group interfaces. Conceptual rows in this table are created and destroyed by the system. The system automatically creates a row in this table for each applicable row in the TIMETRA-SERV-MIB::iesIfTable; currently, applicable rows have the value of iesIfType is equal to 'group' and the value of iesIfGroupInterfaceType is equal to 'lns' or 'softGre'. Deletion of such a row in the iesIfTable results in the same fate for the corresponding row in this table.

svcIfSapCfgEntry.name: svcIfSapCfgEntry
svcIfSapCfgEntry.description: SAP configuration applicable to internal SAP's associated with a specific group interface. Unlike regular subscriber traffic, that enters the system through Service Access Points (SAP) on a group-interface, some user traffic enters the system through a plain layer 3 interface; this traffic is relayed for processing to an ISA MDA; it re-enters through an internal SAP on an internal group interface; this entry allows to configure certain SAP parameters for those internal SAP's. Current examples of such traffic are - traffic for PPP subscriber sessions terminated by the LNS function, - Wifi offload traffic, entering the system through a Soft-GRE tunnel.

svcIfSapCfgLastMgmtChange.name: svcIfSapCfgLastMgmtChange
svcIfSapCfgLastMgmtChange.description: The value of svcIfSapCfgLastMgmtChange indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the most recent management-initiated change to this table row.

svcIfSapCfgDescription.name: svcIfSapCfgDescription
svcIfSapCfgDescription.description: The value of svcIfSapCfgDescription specifies the description of this conceptual row.

svcIfSapCfgDefSubProfile.name: svcIfSapCfgDefSubProfile
svcIfSapCfgDefSubProfile.description: The value of svcIfSapCfgDefSubProfile specifies the default subscriber profile.

svcIfSapCfgDefSlaProfile.name: svcIfSapCfgDefSlaProfile
svcIfSapCfgDefSlaProfile.description: The value of svcIfSapCfgDefSlaProfile specifies the default SLA profile.

svcIfSapCfgDefAppProfile.name: svcIfSapCfgDefAppProfile
svcIfSapCfgDefAppProfile.description: The value of svcIfSapCfgDefSlaProfile specifies the default application profile.

svcIfSapCfgSubIdentPolicy.name: svcIfSapCfgSubIdentPolicy
svcIfSapCfgSubIdentPolicy.description: The value of svcIfSapCfgSubIdentPolicy specifies the subscriber identification policy.

svcIfSapCfgDefSubIdent.name: svcIfSapCfgDefSubIdent
svcIfSapCfgDefSubIdent.description: The value of svcIfSapCfgDefSubIdent specifies the default subscriber identification. This value is used in case no other source (like Radius) provides a subscriber identification string. If the value of this object is set to 'useSapId', the SAP-id will be used as the default subscriber identification string; in this case, svcIfSapCfgDefSubIdentString must contain the empty string, so any non-empty string in svcIfSapCfgDefSubIdentString will be set to an empty string. If the value of this object is set to 'useAutoId', the auto-generated subscriber identification string, as defined in tmnxSubMgmtAutoSubIdObjs, is used as the default subscriber identification string. In this case, svcIfSapCfgDefSubIdentString must contain the empty string, so any non-empty string in svcIfSapCfgDefSubIdentString will be set to an empty string. If the value of this object is set to 'useString', the value of svcIfSapCfgDefSubIdentString will be used as the default subscriber identification string; in this case, an empty svcIfSapCfgDefSubIdentString means that there is no default subscriber identification configured.

svcIfSapCfgDefSubIdentString.name: svcIfSapCfgDefSubIdentString
svcIfSapCfgDefSubIdentString.description: The value of svcIfSapCfgDefSubIdentString specifies the default subscriber identification string.

svcIfSapCfgDefFilterProfile.name: svcIfSapCfgDefFilterProfile
svcIfSapCfgDefFilterProfile.description: The value of the object svcIfSapCfgDefFilterProfile specifies the default filter profile. The specified filter profile needs to exists in the TIMETRA-SUBSCRIBER-MGMT-MIB::tmnxSubFilterProfileTable.

svcTlsSpbUserSvcTable.name: svcTlsSpbUserSvcTable
svcTlsSpbUserSvcTable.description: The svcTlsSpbUserSvcTable contains entries for user VPLS for each control VPLS per forwarding data-base identifier.

svcTlsSpbUserSvcEntry.name: svcTlsSpbUserSvcEntry
svcTlsSpbUserSvcEntry.description: The svcTlsSpbUserSvcEntry contains user VPLS information for each control VPLS per forwarding data-base identfier.

svcTlsSpbUserSvcId.name: svcTlsSpbUserSvcId
svcTlsSpbUserSvcId.description: The value of svcTlsSpbUserSvcId is used for the creation and deletion of provider-tunnel context in a VPLS service.

svcTlsSpbUserSvcLastUpdate.name: svcTlsSpbUserSvcLastUpdate
svcTlsSpbUserSvcLastUpdate.description: The value of svcTlsSpbUserSvcLastUpdate indicates the sysUpTime at the time this entry was last updated.

tlsSpbFdbTable.name: tlsSpbFdbTable
tlsSpbFdbTable.description: The tlsSpbFdbTable contains user VPLS Shortest Path Bridging (SPB) Forwarding Data-Base (FDB) information.

tlsSpbFdbEntry.name: tlsSpbFdbEntry
tlsSpbFdbEntry.description: The tlsSpbFdbEntry contains a specific user VPLS SPB FDB mac-address related information.

tlsSpbFdbMacAddr.name: tlsSpbFdbMacAddr
tlsSpbFdbMacAddr.description: The value of the object tlsSpbFdbMacAddr indicates the 48-bit IEEE 802.3 MAC address.

tlsSpbFdbLocale.name: tlsSpbFdbLocale
tlsSpbFdbLocale.description: The value of the object tlsSpbFdbLocale indicates locality of the this FDB entry.

tlsSpbFdbPortId.name: tlsSpbFdbPortId
tlsSpbFdbPortId.description: The value of tlsSpbFdbPortId indicates the port-id of the SAP for this FDB entry. This object is valid only when tlsSpbFdbLocale is set to 'sap'. This object is otherwise insignificant and should contain a value of 0.

tlsSpbFdbEncapValue.name: tlsSpbFdbEncapValue
tlsSpbFdbEncapValue.description: The value of tlsSpbFdbEncapValue indicates the encap-value of the SAP for this FDB entry. This object is valid only when tlsSpbFdbLocale is set to 'sap'. This object is otherwise insignificant and should contain a value of 0.

tlsSpbFdbSdpId.name: tlsSpbFdbSdpId
tlsSpbFdbSdpId.description: The value of tlsSpbFdbSdpId indicates the sdp identifier of the SDP binding of the SDP for this FDB entry. This object is valid only when tlsSpbFdbLocale is set to 'sdp'. This object is other-wise insignificant and should contain a value of 0.

tlsSpbFdbVcId.name: tlsSpbFdbVcId
tlsSpbFdbVcId.description: The value of tlsSpbFdbPortId indicates the virtual-circuit identifier (vc-id) of the SDP binding of the SDP for this FDB entry. This object is valid only when tlsSpbFdbLocale is set to 'sdp'. This object is other-wise insignificant and should contain a value of 0.

tlsSpbFdbState.name: tlsSpbFdbState
tlsSpbFdbState.description: The tlsSpbFdbState indicates the state of this FDB entry in the user VPLS.

tlsSpbFdbMLocale.name: tlsSpbFdbMLocale
tlsSpbFdbMLocale.description: The value of the object tlsSpbFdbMLocale indicates locality of this FDB entry for multicast traffic.

tlsSpbFdbMPortId.name: tlsSpbFdbMPortId
tlsSpbFdbMPortId.description: The value of tlsSpbFdbMPortId indicates the port-id of the SAP for this FDB entry for multicast traffic. This object is valid only when tlsSpbFdbMLocale is set to 'sap'. This object is otherwise insignificant and should contain a value of 0.

tlsSpbFdbMEncapValue.name: tlsSpbFdbMEncapValue
tlsSpbFdbMEncapValue.description: The value of tlsSpbFdbMEncapValue indicates the encap-value of the SAP for this FDB entry for multicast traffic. This object is valid only when tlsSpbFdbMLocale is set to 'sap'. This object is otherwise insignificant and should contain a value of 0.

tlsSpbFdbMSdpId.name: tlsSpbFdbMSdpId
tlsSpbFdbMSdpId.description: The value of tlsSpbFdbMSdpId indicates the sdp identifier of the SDP binding of the SDP for this FDB entry for multicast traffic. This object is valid only when tlsSpbFdbMLocale is set to 'sdp'. This object is other-wise insignificant and should contain a value of 0.

tlsSpbFdbMVcId.name: tlsSpbFdbMVcId
tlsSpbFdbMVcId.description: The value of tlsSpbFdbMPortId indicates the virtual-circuit identifier (vc-id) of the SDP binding of the SDP for this FDB entry for multicast traffic. This object is valid only when tlsSpbFdbMLocale is set to 'sdp'. This object is other-wise insignificant and should contain a value of 0.

tlsSpbFdbMState.name: tlsSpbFdbMState
tlsSpbFdbMState.description: The tlsSpbFdbMState indicates the state of this FDB entry for multicast traffic in the user VPLS.

tlsSpbFidFdbTable.name: tlsSpbFidFdbTable
tlsSpbFidFdbTable.description: The tlsSpbFidFdbTable contains control VPLS Shortest Path Bridging (SPB) Forwarding Data-Base (FDB) information.

tlsSpbFidFdbEntry.name: tlsSpbFidFdbEntry
tlsSpbFidFdbEntry.description: The tlsSpbFidFdbEntry contains a specific control VPLS SPB FDB mac-address related information.

tlsSpbFidFdbMacAddr.name: tlsSpbFidFdbMacAddr
tlsSpbFidFdbMacAddr.description: The value of the object tlsSpbFidFdbMacAddr indicates the 48-bit IEEE 802.3 MAC address.

tlsSpbFidFdbLocale.name: tlsSpbFidFdbLocale
tlsSpbFidFdbLocale.description: The value of the object tlsSpbFidFdbLocale indicates locality of the this FDB entry.

tlsSpbFidFdbPortId.name: tlsSpbFidFdbPortId
tlsSpbFidFdbPortId.description: The value of tlsSpbFidFdbPortId indicates the port-id of the SAP for this FDB entry. This object is valid only when tlsSpbFidFdbLocale is set to 'sap'. This object is otherwise insignificant and should contain a value of 0.

tlsSpbFidFdbEncapValue.name: tlsSpbFidFdbEncapValue
tlsSpbFidFdbEncapValue.description: The value of tlsSpbFidFdbEncapValue indicates the encap-value of the SAP for this FDB entry. This object is valid only when tlsSpbFidFdbLocale is set to 'sap'. This object is otherwise insignificant and should contain a value of 0.

tlsSpbFidFdbSdpId.name: tlsSpbFidFdbSdpId
tlsSpbFidFdbSdpId.description: The value of tlsSpbFidFdbSdpId indicates the sdp identifier of the SDP binding of the SDP for this FDB entry. This object is valid only when tlsSpbFidFdbLocale is set to 'sdp'. This object is other-wise insignificant and should contain a value of 0.

tlsSpbFidFdbVcId.name: tlsSpbFidFdbVcId
tlsSpbFidFdbVcId.description: The value of tlsSpbFidFdbPortId indicates the virtual-circuit identifier (vc-id) of the SDP binding of the SDP for this FDB entry. This object is valid only when tlsSpbFidFdbLocale is set to 'sdp'. This object is other-wise insignificant and should contain a value of 0.

tlsSpbFidFdbMLocale.name: tlsSpbFidFdbMLocale
tlsSpbFidFdbMLocale.description: The value of the object tlsSpbFidFdbMLocale indicates locality of the this FDB entry for multicast traffic.

tlsSpbFidFdbMPortId.name: tlsSpbFidFdbMPortId
tlsSpbFidFdbMPortId.description: The value of tlsSpbFidFdbMPortId indicates the port-id of the SAP for this FDB entry for multicast traffic. This object is valid only when tlsSpbFidFdbMLocale is set to 'sap'. This object is otherwise insignificant and should contain a value of 0.

tlsSpbFidFdbMEncapValue.name: tlsSpbFidFdbMEncapValue
tlsSpbFidFdbMEncapValue.description: The value of tlsSpbFidFdbMEncapValue indicates the encap-value of the SAP for this FDB entry for multicast traffic. This object is valid only when tlsSpbFidFdbMLocale is set to 'sap'. This object is otherwise insignificant and should contain a value of 0.

tlsSpbFidFdbMSdpId.name: tlsSpbFidFdbMSdpId
tlsSpbFidFdbMSdpId.description: The value of tlsSpbFidFdbMSdpId indicates the sdp identifier of the SDP binding of the SDP for this FDB entry for multicast traffic. This object is valid only when tlsSpbFidFdbMLocale is set to 'sdp'. This object is other-wise insignificant and should contain a value of 0.

tlsSpbFidFdbMVcId.name: tlsSpbFidFdbMVcId
tlsSpbFidFdbMVcId.description: The value of tlsSpbFidFdbMPortId indicates the virtual-circuit identifier (vc-id) of the SDP binding of the SDP for this FDB entry for multicast traffic. This object is valid only when tlsSpbFidFdbMLocale is set to 'sdp'. This object is other-wise insignificant and should contain a value of 0.

tlsSpbFidFdbLastUpdate.name: tlsSpbFidFdbLastUpdate
tlsSpbFidFdbLastUpdate.description: The value of tlsSpbFidFdbLastUpdate indicates the sysUpTime at the time unicast SAP/SDP information of this entry was last updated.

tlsSpbFidFdbMLastUpdate.name: tlsSpbFidFdbMLastUpdate
tlsSpbFidFdbMLastUpdate.description: The value of tlsSpbFidFdbLastUpdate indicates the sysUpTime at the time multicast SAP/SDP information of this entry was last updated.

tlsSpbMFibTable.name: tlsSpbMFibTable
tlsSpbMFibTable.description: The tlsSpbMFibTable contains user VPLS Shortest Path Bridging (SPB) multicast forwarding data-base (Mfib) information.

tlsSpbMFibEntry.name: tlsSpbMFibEntry
tlsSpbMFibEntry.description: The tlsSpbMFibEntry contains an entry for specific SAP or SDP in the multicast forwarding data-base of the user VPLS for the group MAC address.

tlsSpbMFibMacAddr.name: tlsSpbMFibMacAddr
tlsSpbMFibMacAddr.description: The value of the object tlsSpbMFibMacAddr indicates the 48-bit IEEE 802.3 group MAC address.

tlsSpbMFibIsid.name: tlsSpbMFibIsid
tlsSpbMFibIsid.description: The value of tlsSpbMFibIsid indicates the value of ISID of the group MAC address of this entry.

tlsSpbMFibState.name: tlsSpbMFibState
tlsSpbMFibState.description: The tlsSpbMFibState indicates the state of this FDB entry in the user VPLS.

tlsSpbFidMFibTable.name: tlsSpbFidMFibTable
tlsSpbFidMFibTable.description: The tlsSpbFidMFibTable contains control VPLS Shortest Path Bridging (SPB) multicast forwarding data-base (MFib) information.

tlsSpbFidMFibEntry.name: tlsSpbFidMFibEntry
tlsSpbFidMFibEntry.description: The tlsSpbFidMFibEntry contains an entry for specific SAP or SDP in the multicast forwarding data-base of the controlling vpls for the group MAC address.

tlsSpbFidMFibMacAddr.name: tlsSpbFidMFibMacAddr
tlsSpbFidMFibMacAddr.description: The value of the object tlsSpbFidMFibMacAddr indicates the 48-bit IEEE 802.3 group MAC address.

tlsSpbFidMFibLocale.name: tlsSpbFidMFibLocale
tlsSpbFidMFibLocale.description: The value of the object tlsSpbFidMFibLocale indicates locality of the this FDB entry.

tlsSpbFidMFibPortId.name: tlsSpbFidMFibPortId
tlsSpbFidMFibPortId.description: The value of tlsSpbFidMFibPortId indicates the port-id of the SAP for this multicast forwarding data-base (MFIB) entry. This object is valid only when tlsSpbFidFdbLocale is set to 'sap'. This object is otherwise insignificant and should contain a value of 0.

tlsSpbFidMFibEncapValue.name: tlsSpbFidMFibEncapValue
tlsSpbFidMFibEncapValue.description: The value of tlsSpbFidMFibEncapValue indicates the encap-value of the SAP for this multicast forwarding data-base (MFIB) entry. This object is valid only when tlsSpbFidFdbLocale is set to 'sap'. This object is otherwise insignificant and should contain a value of 0.

tlsSpbFidMFibSdpId.name: tlsSpbFidMFibSdpId
tlsSpbFidMFibSdpId.description: The value of tlsSpbFidMFibSdpId indicates the sdp identifier of the SDP binding of the SDP for this FDB entry. This object is valid only when tlsSpbFidMFibLocale is set to 'sdp'. This object is other-wise insignificant and should contain a value of 0.

tlsSpbFidMFibVcId.name: tlsSpbFidMFibVcId
tlsSpbFidMFibVcId.description: The value of tlsSpbFidMFibPortId indicates the virtual-circuit identifier (vc-id) of the SDP binding of the SDP for this FDB entry. This object is valid only when tlsSpbFidMFibLocale is set to 'sdp'. This object is other-wise insignificant and should contain a value of 0.

tlsSpbFidMFibIsid.name: tlsSpbFidMFibIsid
tlsSpbFidMFibIsid.description: The value of tlsSpbFidMFibIsid indicates the value of ISID of the group MAC address of this entry.

tlsSpbFidMFibLastUpdate.name: tlsSpbFidMFibLastUpdate
tlsSpbFidMFibLastUpdate.description: The value of tlsSpbFidMFibLastUpdate indicates the sysUpTime at the time this entry was last updated.

svcSpbIfTable.name: svcSpbIfTable
svcSpbIfTable.description: The svcSpbIfTable contains Shortest Path Bridging (SPB) interface information.

svcSpbIfEntry.name: svcSpbIfEntry
svcSpbIfEntry.description: The svcSpbIfEntry contains a specific SPB interface related information.

svcSpbIfIndex.name: svcSpbIfIndex
svcSpbIfIndex.description: The value of the object svcSpbIfIndex indicates the interface index.

svcSpbIfLocale.name: svcSpbIfLocale
svcSpbIfLocale.description: The value of the object svcSpbIfLocale indicates locality of the this interface entry.

svcSpbIfPortId.name: svcSpbIfPortId
svcSpbIfPortId.description: The value of svcSpbIfPortId indicates the port-id of the SAP for this interface entry. This object is valid only when svcSpbIfLocale is set to 'sap'. This object is otherwise insignificant and should contain a value of 0.

svcSpbIfEncapValue.name: svcSpbIfEncapValue
svcSpbIfEncapValue.description: The value of svcSpbIfEncapValue indicates the encap-value of the SAP for this interface entry. This object is valid only when svcSpbIfLocale is set to 'sap'. This object is otherwise insignificant and should contain a value of 0.

svcSpbIfSdpId.name: svcSpbIfSdpId
svcSpbIfSdpId.description: The value of svcSpbIfSdpId indicates the sdp identifier of the SDP binding of the SDP for this interface entry. This object is valid only when svcSpbIfLocale is set to 'sdp'. This object is other-wise insignificant and should contain a value of 0.

svcSpbIfVcId.name: svcSpbIfVcId
svcSpbIfVcId.description: The value of svcSpbIfPortId indicates the virtual-circuit identifier (vc-id) of the SDP binding of the SDP for this interface entry. This object is valid only when svcSpbIfLocale is set to 'sdp'. This object is other-wise insignificant and should contain a value of 0.

svcSpbIfSvcId.name: svcSpbIfSvcId
svcSpbIfSvcId.description: The value of svcSpbIfSvcId indicates the service identifier of this Shortest Path Bridging interface.

svcSpbIfIsisInstance.name: svcSpbIfIsisInstance
svcSpbIfIsisInstance.description: The value of svcSpbIfIsisInstance indicates the ISIS-MIB::isisSysInstance used with this Shortest Path Bridging interface.

svcArpHostOvrTable.name: svcArpHostOvrTable
svcArpHostOvrTable.description: The svcArpHostOvrTable contains QoS (Quality of Service) overrides for ARP hosts. Entries in this table are created and destroyed by the system. This table is a sparse augment of the svcArpHostTable: entries are created only for ARH hosts for which QoS overrides information is available.

svcArpHostOvrEntry.name: svcArpHostOvrEntry
svcArpHostOvrEntry.description: Each conceptual row represents QoS overrides information of an ARP Host.

svcArpHostOvrDirection.name: svcArpHostOvrDirection
svcArpHostOvrDirection.description: The value of svcArpHostOvrDirection indicates if this row specifies ingress or egress qos override parameters.

svcArpHostOvrType.name: svcArpHostOvrType
svcArpHostOvrType.description: The value of svcArpHostOvrType indicates what field has been overridden by this row.

svcArpHostOvrTypeId.name: svcArpHostOvrTypeId
svcArpHostOvrTypeId.description: The value of svcArpHostOvrTypeId indicates the ID of the queue/policer that has been overridden by this row. If the value of svcArpHostOvrType is not 'queue (1)' or 'policer (2)', this field must be set to zero (0).

svcArpHostOvrTypeName.name: svcArpHostOvrTypeName
svcArpHostOvrTypeName.description: The value of svcArpHostOvrTypeName indicates the name of the scheduler/arbiter that has been overridden by this row. If the value of svcArpHostOvrType is not 'arbiter (4)' or 'scheduler (5)', this field must be set to zero (0).

svcArpHostOvrPIR.name: svcArpHostOvrPIR
svcArpHostOvrPIR.description: The value of svcArpHostOvrPIR indicates the PIR rate in kbps allowed for the object overridden by this row.

svcArpHostOvrCIR.name: svcArpHostOvrCIR
svcArpHostOvrCIR.description: The value of svcArpHostOvrCIR indicates the CIR rate in kbps allowed for the object overridden by this row.

svcArpHostOvrCBS.name: svcArpHostOvrCBS
svcArpHostOvrCBS.description: The value of svcArpHostOvrCBS indicates the amount of reserved buffer space (in bytes) for the object overridden by this row.

svcArpHostOvrMBS.name: svcArpHostOvrMBS
svcArpHostOvrMBS.description: The value of svcArpHostOvrMBS indicates the maximum amount of reserved buffer space (in bytes) for the object overridden by this row.

svcArpHostOvrWrrWeight.name: svcArpHostOvrWrrWeight
svcArpHostOvrWrrWeight.description: The value of svcArpHostOvrWrrWeight specifies the weight of this queue for the HSMDA scheduler. The weight determines how much bandwidth this queue gets out of the total rate for the scheduling class. The value of svcArpHostOvrWrrWeight is only relevant if the value of svcArpHostOvrType is equal to 'queue', and if the queue specified in svcArpHostOvrTypeId is referenced in the value of TIMETRA-QOS-MIB::tHsmdaWrrPolicyIncludeQueues of the Weighted Round Robin policy associated with this ARP Host.

iesIfIsaTnlNHTableLastChanged.name: iesIfIsaTnlNHTableLastChanged
iesIfIsaTnlNHTableLastChanged.description: The value of iesIfIsaTnlNHTableLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of iesIfIsaTnlNHTable. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

iesIfIsaTnlNHTable.name: iesIfIsaTnlNHTable
iesIfIsaTnlNHTable.description: The iesIfIsaTnlNHTable contains entries for IES interface ISA tunnel next-hop information in an IES service context.

iesIfIsaTnlNHEntry.name: iesIfIsaTnlNHEntry
iesIfIsaTnlNHEntry.description: The iesIfIsaTnlNHEntry contains IES service ISA tunnel next-hop information per service interface.

iesIfIsaTnlNHLastChanged.name: iesIfIsaTnlNHLastChanged
iesIfIsaTnlNHLastChanged.description: The value of iesIfIsaTnlNHLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of this entry. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

iesIfIsaTnlNHStaticAddrType.name: iesIfIsaTnlNHStaticAddrType
iesIfIsaTnlNHStaticAddrType.description: The value of iesIfIsaTnlNHStaticAddrType specifies the address type of iesIfIsaTnlNHStaticAddr object.

iesIfIsaTnlNHStaticAddr.name: iesIfIsaTnlNHStaticAddr
iesIfIsaTnlNHStaticAddr.description: The value of iesIfIsaTnlNHStaticAddr specifies the IP address of the redundant next-hop for static ISA tunnels on this interface.

iesIfIsaTnlNHDynAddrType.name: iesIfIsaTnlNHDynAddrType
iesIfIsaTnlNHDynAddrType.description: The value of iesIfIsaTnlNHDynAddrType specifies the address type of iesIfIsaTnlNHStaticAddr object.

iesIfIsaTnlNHDynAddr.name: iesIfIsaTnlNHDynAddr
iesIfIsaTnlNHDynAddr.description: The value of iesIfIsaTnlNHDynAddr specifies the IP address of the redundant next-hop for dynamic ISA tunnels on this interface.

macPinningMacAddress.name: macPinningMacAddress
macPinningMacAddress.description: The value of the object macPinningMacAddress indicates the pinned MAC address.

macPinningPinnedRow.name: macPinningPinnedRow
macPinningPinnedRow.description: The value of the object macPinningPinnedRow indicates where the MAC address is currently pinned on. Its value will be the OID of the first accessible object in the row of the sapTlsInfoTable or in the sdpBindTable, depending on whether the MAC address is pinned on a SAP or a SDP Bind.

macPinningPinnedRowDescr.name: macPinningPinnedRowDescr
